name: CCI 550 Small Pistol Magnum Primers #0018 (1000)
description:
The CCI 550 Small Pistol Magnum Primers #0018 are one of the replaceable parts of the cartridge; found at the bottom of the cartridge case, its function being to ignite the main powder charge. Magnum primers are intended for large-capacity cases and/or ball propellants.

Once struck by the firing pin the primer ignites the main powder charge, firing the bullet! The primer is found at the base of the cartridge case and is a replaceable part of the cartridge during reloading. CCI Primers utilise non-corrosive and non-mercuric initiator mixes selected for their clean burning characteristics.

All CCI Primers have a larger anvil area to compensate for firearms that may have an off-centre firing pin and are engineered to enable smooth feeding in automated reloading equipment.

Large cases, cold weather, and certain propellants often require a hotter primer flame and a longer burn than that provided by a standard primer. The CCI 250 Large Rifle Magnum Primers offer an increase of ~23% hotter flame over standard, with an increased flame duration.

Note that Magnum primers should be used only where specified in published reloading manuals/data or where loads are specifically developed with these primers.

name: Glock G17 Gen 3 9x19 Standard Pistol
description:
The Glock G17 Gen 3 9x19 Standard Pistol is a modern firearm with a lightweight polymer frame, chambered for 9mm Luger (9mm P, 9 x 19mm) calibre ammunition. This third generation handgun holds 17 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity magazines are available.

Glock Safe-Action pistols were introduced in the 1980's and have excelled in military, police and civilian environments. The Glock was the first commercially successful polymer framed handgun. Initially offered in 9x19mm Glock pistols are now available in many other calibres too.

With several different sizes available, there is a Glock to suit almost any requirement. Long-slide models are great for competition, standard models are well suited for officers on duty, for example, and the compact, sub-compact or slimline models offer a balanced, self-defence capability. Their versatility ensures that most models are multi-functional, serving well for home defence, daily carry, duty or competition!

The polymer frame and grip is tough, lightweight and corrosion resistant. Tenifer, the 'nearly hard as diamond' Glock surface treatment, protects the barrel and slide while remaining anti-reflective.

Shooting Stuff recommends Glock pistols! With minimal external controls they are extremely easy to use and to learn to use, for left-handed and right-handed shooters! They are reliable, durable and lightweight. Three independent, automatic safety features ensure that the pistol fires when, and only when, the trigger is deliberately pulled. All three safety features re-engage when the trigger is released, automatically securing the pistol again. We believe that Glock is the best supported firearms brand in South Africa, with spares, magazines, holsters and many aftermarket accessories available ex-stock.

Three automatic safety features:

  1. The trigger safety prevents inadvertent firing by lateral force on the trigger, and is automatically depressed when initial tension is applied to the trigger. It automatically resets when the trigger is released.
  • The firing pin safety is a hardened steel plunger that blocks the firing pin from igniting the chambered cartridge until the trigger is pulled to the rear, pushing the firing pin safety up and out of the way. It automatically reactivates when the trigger is released.
  • The drop safety prevents the trigger mechanism from "activating" and firing an unintentional shot in the event that the pistol drops or falls onto a hard surface. Only with sufficient rearward travel of the trigger can the firing pin be released, firing the shot.

    • The extractor serves as a loaded chamber indicator, and the trigger offers further visual and tactile cues to the gun's status.

    Standard models are well suited to open carry by law enforcement officers, and remain popular with competition shooters and larger framed people for concealed carry.

name: Glock G17 Gen 4 SILC 9x19 Standard Pistol
description:
The Glock G17 Gen 4 SILC 9x19 Standard Pistol is a modern firearm with a lightweight polymer frame, chambered for 9mm Luger (9mm P, 9 x 19mm) calibre ammunition. This fourth generation handgun holds 17 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity magazines are available. The SILC-models have an extended barrel, threaded for an accessory such as a silencer, or compensator.

Glock Safe-Action pistols were introduced in the 1980's and have excelled in military, police and civilian environments. The Glock was the first commercially successful polymer framed handgun. Initially offered in 9x19mm Glock pistols are now available in many other calibres too.

With several different sizes available, there is a Glock to suit almost any requirement. Long-slide models are great for competition, standard models are well suited for officers on duty, for example, and the compact, sub-compact or slimline models offer a balanced, self-defence capability. Their versatility ensures that most models are multi-functional, serving well for home defence, daily carry, duty or competition!

The polymer frame and grip is tough, lightweight and corrosion resistant. Tenifer, the 'nearly hard as diamond' Glock surface treatment, protects the barrel and slide while remaining anti-reflective.

Shooting Stuff recommends Glock pistols! With minimal external controls they are extremely easy to use and to learn to use, for left-handed and right-handed shooters! They are reliable, durable and lightweight. Three independent, automatic safety features ensure that the pistol fires when, and only when, the trigger is deliberately pulled. All three safety features re-engage when the trigger is released, automatically securing the pistol again. We believe that Glock is the best supported firearms brand in South Africa, with spares, magazines, holsters and many aftermarket accessories available ex-stock.

Three automatic safety features:

  1. The trigger safety prevents inadvertent firing by lateral force on the trigger, and is automatically depressed when initial tension is applied to the trigger. It automatically resets when the trigger is released.
  • The firing pin safety is a hardened steel plunger that blocks the firing pin from igniting the chambered cartridge until the trigger is pulled to the rear, pushing the firing pin safety up and out of the way. It automatically reactivates when the trigger is released.
  • The drop safety prevents the trigger mechanism from "activating" and firing an unintentional shot in the event that the pistol drops or falls onto a hard surface. Only with sufficient rearward travel of the trigger can the firing pin be released, firing the shot.

    • The extractor serves as a loaded chamber indicator, and the trigger offers further visual and tactile cues to the gun's status.

    Standard models are well suited to open carry by law enforcement officers, and remain popular with competition shooters and larger framed people for concealed carry.

name: Glock G30 Gen 4 .45 ACP Compact Pistol
description:
The Glock G30 Gen 4 .45 ACP Compact Pistol is a modern firearm with a lightweight polymer frame, chambered for 45 Auto (ACP) calibre ammunition. This fourth generation handgun holds 10 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity magazines are available.

Glock Safe-Action pistols were introduced in the 1980's and have excelled in military, police and civilian environments. The Glock was the first commercially successful polymer framed handgun. Initially offered in 9x19mm Glock pistols are now available in many other calibres too.

With several different sizes available, there is a Glock to suit almost any requirement. Long-slide models are great for competition, standard models are well suited for officers on duty, for example, and the compact, sub-compact or slimline models offer a balanced, self-defence capability. Their versatility ensures that most models are multi-functional, serving well for home defence, daily carry, duty or competition!

The polymer frame and grip is tough, lightweight and corrosion resistant. Tenifer, the 'nearly hard as diamond' Glock surface treatment, protects the barrel and slide while remaining anti-reflective.

Shooting Stuff recommends Glock pistols! With minimal external controls they are extremely easy to use and to learn to use, for left-handed and right-handed shooters! They are reliable, durable and lightweight. Three independent, automatic safety features ensure that the pistol fires when, and only when, the trigger is deliberately pulled. All three safety features re-engage when the trigger is released, automatically securing the pistol again. We believe that Glock is the best supported firearms brand in South Africa, with spares, magazines, holsters and many aftermarket accessories available ex-stock.

Three automatic safety features:

  1. The trigger safety prevents inadvertent firing by lateral force on the trigger, and is automatically depressed when initial tension is applied to the trigger. It automatically resets when the trigger is released.
  • The firing pin safety is a hardened steel plunger that blocks the firing pin from igniting the chambered cartridge until the trigger is pulled to the rear, pushing the firing pin safety up and out of the way. It automatically reactivates when the trigger is released.
  • The drop safety prevents the trigger mechanism from "activating" and firing an unintentional shot in the event that the pistol drops or falls onto a hard surface. Only with sufficient rearward travel of the trigger can the firing pin be released, firing the shot.

    • The extractor serves as a loaded chamber indicator, and the trigger offers further visual and tactile cues to the gun's status.

    Compact models are most versatile, offering a great balance between open carry, concealed carry and range use. The integrated mounting rail allows quick and convenient mounting / dismounting of accessories like tactical torches and lasers.

name: Glock G35 Gen 4 .40 S&W Competition Pistol
description:
The Glock G35 Gen 4 .40 S&W; Competition Pistol is a modern firearm with a lightweight polymer frame, chambered for 40 S&W; calibre ammunition. This fourth generation handgun holds 15 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity magazines are available. This model is designed specifically to comply with IPSC Standard Gun size limitations.

Glock Safe-Action pistols were introduced in the 1980's and have excelled in military, police and civilian environments. The Glock was the first commercially successful polymer framed handgun. Initially offered in 9x19mm Glock pistols are now available in many other calibres too.

With several different sizes available, there is a Glock to suit almost any requirement. Long-slide models are great for competition, standard models are well suited for officers on duty, for example, and the compact, sub-compact or slimline models offer a balanced, self-defence capability. Their versatility ensures that most models are multi-functional, serving well for home defence, daily carry, duty or competition!

The polymer frame and grip is tough, lightweight and corrosion resistant. Tenifer, the 'nearly hard as diamond' Glock surface treatment, protects the barrel and slide while remaining anti-reflective.

Shooting Stuff recommends Glock pistols! With minimal external controls they are extremely easy to use and to learn to use, for left-handed and right-handed shooters! They are reliable, durable and lightweight. Three independent, automatic safety features ensure that the pistol fires when, and only when, the trigger is deliberately pulled. All three safety features re-engage when the trigger is released, automatically securing the pistol again. We believe that Glock is the best supported firearms brand in South Africa, with spares, magazines, holsters and many aftermarket accessories available ex-stock.

Three automatic safety features:

  1. The trigger safety prevents inadvertent firing by lateral force on the trigger, and is automatically depressed when initial tension is applied to the trigger. It automatically resets when the trigger is released.
  • The firing pin safety is a hardened steel plunger that blocks the firing pin from igniting the chambered cartridge until the trigger is pulled to the rear, pushing the firing pin safety up and out of the way. It automatically reactivates when the trigger is released.
  • The drop safety prevents the trigger mechanism from "activating" and firing an unintentional shot in the event that the pistol drops or falls onto a hard surface. Only with sufficient rearward travel of the trigger can the firing pin be released, firing the shot.

    • The extractor serves as a loaded chamber indicator, and the trigger offers further visual and tactile cues to the gun's status.

    The extended barrel length and longer sight radius of the competition models offer greater precision to competitive shooters and special units.

With several different sizes available, there is a Glock to suit almost any requirement. Long-slide models are great for competition, standard models are well suited for officers on duty, for example, and the compact, sub-compact or slimline models offer a balanced, self-defence capability. Their versatility ensures that most models are multi-functional, serving well for home defence, daily carry, duty or competition!

The polymer frame and grip is tough, lightweight and corrosion resistant. Tenifer, the 'nearly hard as diamond' Glock surface treatment, protects the barrel and slide while remaining anti-reflective.

Shooting Stuff recommends Glock pistols! With minimal external controls they are extremely easy to use and to learn to use, for left-handed and right-handed shooters! They are reliable, durable and lightweight. Three independent, automatic safety features ensure that the pistol fires when, and only when, the trigger is deliberately pulled. All three safety features re-engage when the trigger is released, automatically securing the pistol again. We believe that Glock is the best supported firearms brand in South Africa, with spares, magazines, holsters and many aftermarket accessories available ex-stock.

Three automatic safety features: 

  1. The trigger safety prevents inadvertent firing by lateral force on the trigger, and is automatically depressed when initial tension is applied to the trigger. It automatically resets when the trigger is released.
  2. The firing pin safety is a hardened steel plunger that blocks the firing pin from igniting the chambered cartridge until the trigger is pulled to the rear, pushing the firing pin safety up and out of the way. It automatically reactivates when the trigger is released.
  3. The drop safety prevents the trigger mechanism from "activating" and firing an unintentional shot in the event that the pistol drops or falls onto a hard surface. Only with sufficient rearward travel of the trigger can the firing pin be released, firing the shot.

 The extractor serves as a loaded chamber indicator, and the trigger offers further visual and tactile cues to the gun's status.

Glock Slimline models are highly concealable, full-powered pistols that remain comfortable to shoot. Their small size does preclude the integrated accessory rail! Unlike most other models the Slimline models feature single-stack magazines..

name: CZ 75 B Omega 9x19 Standard Pistol
description:
The CZ 75 B Omega 9x19 Standard Pistol is a proven firearm with a traditional steel frame, chambered for 9mm Luger (9mm P, 9 x 19mm) calibre ammunition. This handgun holds 16 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity magazines are available.

The timeless CZ 75 is the mainstay from the Czech firearms company, and modern variants now include the revolutionary Omega trigger mechanism.

Safety features include an ambidextrous, manually operated, frame-mounted safety catch and an automatic firing pin block.

The top of the slide is enhanced with an anti-reflection coating for better shooting comfort, and is fitted with steel sights that feature contrasting, luminscent dots.

This model has a manually operated, frame-mounted safety catch, not the decocker.

name: CZ P-01 9x19 Compact Pistol
description:
The CZ P-01 9x19 Compact Pistol is a modern evolution of the proven CZ 75 pistol, with a traditional steel frame, chambered for 9mm Luger (9mm P, 9 x 19mm) calibre ammunition. This handgun holds 14 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity magazines are available.

SP-01, the modern range of handguns from the Czech firearms company, includes the baby of that family, the P-01. This pistol is designed for concealed carry, yet features the revolutionary Omega trigger mechanism (from 2016 production).

Safety features include an ambidextrous, manually operated, frame-mounted safety catch / decocker (from 2016 production) and an automatic firing pin block.

The top of the slide is enhanced with anti-reflective serrations for better shooting comfort, and is fitted with steel sights that feature contrasting, luminscent dots. Self-illuminating, Tritium night sights are an available option.

The currently available model (pre-2016) has a manually operated, frame-mounted decocker without the Omega trigger.

name: CZ P-07 Duty 9x19 Compact Pistol
description:
The CZ P-07 Duty 9x19 Compact Pistol is a modern firearm with a lightweight polymer frame, chambered for 9mm Luger (9mm P, 9 x 19mm) calibre ammunition. This first generation handgun holds 15 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity magazines are available.

The CZ P-07 is one of a modern range of polymer-framed handguns from the Czech firearms company. This pistol is designed for concealed carry as well as law-enforcement, yet features the revolutionary Omega trigger mechanism.

Safety features include an ambidextrous, manually operated, frame-mounted safety catch (optionally a decocker) and an automatic firing pin block. All these are built around the proven Omega trigger system.

The slide features front serrations for easy cocking and is fitted with steel sights that feature contrasting, luminscent dots. Self-illuminating, Tritium night sights are an available option. Steel parts have an extremely durable surface finish.

The durable, fibreglass-reinforced polymer frame features an integral accessory rail for weapon-mounted lights, etc. The grip offers interchangeable backstraps that allows the shooter to alter the ergonomics to their preferred grip size - small, medium or large. The magazine release catch is reversible for left-handed shooters.

This first generation model does not feature all of these innovations: No front serrations on the slide. Only the standard safety catch is included. The grip size cannot be altered. Only standard capacity basepads are included for the magazines.

The CZ P-07 is one of a modern range of polymer-framed handguns from the Czech firearms company. This pistol is designed for concealed carry as well as law-enforcement, yet features the revolutionary Omega trigger mechanism.

Safety features include an ambidextrous, manually operated, frame-mounted safety catch (optionally a decocker) and an automatic firing pin block. All these are built around the proven Omega trigger system.

This second generation model features all of these innovations!

name: CZ 75 SP-01 Shadow 9x19 Competition Pistol (Black)
description:
The CZ 75 SP-01 Shadow 9x19 Competition Pistol (Black) is a modern competition firearm with a traditional steel frame, chambered for 9mm Luger (9mm P, 9 x 19mm) calibre ammunition. This handgun holds 18 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity magazines are available.

CZ designers teamed with some of the world's top competitive shooters to create the SP-01 range of full-sized, steel framed pistols from the solid foundation of the venerable CZ 75. While the Shadow dominates the IPSC Production Division, many security forces rely on the superb accuracy and reliability of other SP-01 variants.

The SP-01 range have great ergonomics designed into the grip, for a closer alignment for the bore axis to the hand. The magazine release catch is extended for easier actuation. The steel frame includes an integral MIL-STD-1913 tactical rail ahead of the trigger guard, for weapon mounted lights, etc. A bevelled magazine well assists with easy reloads.

The top of the slide is enhanced with anti-reflective serrations for better shooting comfort, and is fitted with steel sights. All models feature an extended slide stop for easier operation.

The DA/SA trigger allows a typical "long, hard pull" for the first double-action shot, and a fantastic "short, crisp pull" for subsequent shots.

The CZ 75 SP-01 Shadow has a 1.5mm red fibre-optic front sight, plain black Novak-style rear sight. This competition pistol features an ergonomic manual safety catch, but is without a firing pin safety for an improved trigger pull. It comes with checkered rubber grips.
short_description: The CZ 75 SP-01 Shadow 9x19 Competition Pistol (Black) is a modern competition firearm with a traditional steel frame, chambered for 9mm Luger (9mm P, 9 x 19mm) calibre ammunition. This handgun holds 18 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity magazines are available.

While the Shadow dominates the IPSC Production Division, many security forces rely on the superb accuracy and reliability of other SP-01 variants.

The SP-01 range have great ergonomics designed into the grip, for a closer alignment for the bore axis to the hand. The magazine release catch is extended for easier actuation. The steel frame includes an integral MIL-STD-1913 tactical rail ahead of the trigger guard, for weapon mounted lights, etc. A bevelled magazine well assists with easy reloads.

The top of the slide is enhanced with anti-reflective serrations for better shooting comfort, and is fitted with steel sights. All models feature an extended slide stop for easier operation.

The DA/SA trigger allows a typical "long, hard pull" for the first double-action shot, and a fantastic "short, crisp pull" for subsequent shots.

The CZ 75 SP-01 Tactical has Tritium sights, a manual decocker and firing pin safety. This model has checkered rubber grips.

name: CZ 75 TS Czechmate 9mm Mjr Comp Pistol (Black)
description:
The CZ 75 TS Czechmate 9mm Major Competition Pistol (Black) is a modern competition firearm with a traditional steel frame, chambered for 9mm Luger (9mm P, 9 x 19mm) calibre ammunition. This handgun holds 20 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity magazines are available.

The CZ 75 TS (Tactical Sports) is a locked breech pistol, designed for sport shooting. It is offered in two fundamental variants, for IPSC Standard Gun division and for IPSC Open Gun division.

Based on the proven CZ 75 heritage, the TS is bigger with a full dust cover (the frame ahead of the trigger guard), and differs from the original CZ 75 in having only a single action trigger mechanism. The match trigger is adjustable.

The magazine catch is extended for easier operation and the bottom of the grip includes an integral magazine well for easier and quicker reloads.

The Czechmate model (designed for IPSC Open) is offered in 9x19, either 9mm Luger or 9mm Major, with a four-port compensator and includes a C-More red-dot sight installed on a single-sided CZ mount. The Czechmate can quickly be reconfigured for "Standard Gun", by removing the compensator and optical sight (and installing the included steel sights).

name: CZ 75 TS Czechmate 9mm Mjr Comp Pistol (Parrot)
description:
The CZ 75 TS Czechmate 9mm Major Competition Pistol (Parrot) is a modern competition firearm with a traditional steel frame, chambered for 9mm Luger (9mm P, 9 x 19mm) calibre ammunition. This handgun holds 20 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity magazines are available.

The CZ 75 TS (Tactical Sports) is a locked breech pistol, designed for sport shooting. It is offered in two fundamental variants, for IPSC Standard Gun division and for IPSC Open Gun division.

Based on the proven CZ 75 heritage, the TS is bigger with a full dust cover (the frame ahead of the trigger guard), and differs from the original CZ 75 in having only a single action trigger mechanism. The match trigger is adjustable.

The Orange offers enhanced accuracy through the hand fitted, polished barrel mated to a precisely fitted slide with minimum lateral tolerances. The improved single-action trigger mechanism with re-designed hammer further enhances delivered precision.

name: CZ 97 B .45 ACP Standard Pistol
description:
The CZ 97 B .45 ACP Standard Pistol is a proven firearm with a traditional steel frame, chambered for 45 Auto (ACP) calibre ammunition. This handgun holds 10 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine.

A natural evolution of the 9mm CZ 75 into the powerful .45 ACP calibre, the CZ 97 B has been called the most accurate, serially produced 'combat pistol' in .45 ACP.

The DA/SA trigger allows a typical "long, hard pull" for the first double-action shot, and a "short, crisp pull" for subsequent shots. Safety features include a manually operated, frame-mounted safety catch and an automatic firing pin block, as well as a loaded chamber indicator.

The top of the slide is enhanced with anti-reflective serrations for better shooting comfort. The slide has front serrations for easy cocking, and is fitted with steel sights that feature contrasting, luminscent dots.

name: Walther HK-MP5-SD .22 LR Semi-Auto Carbine
description:
The Walther HK-MP5-SD .22 LR Semi-Auto Carbine is a tactical rimfire replica firearm, a copy of the always-suppressed Heckler & Koch MP5 SD 9mm submachine gun. This replica is chambered for 22 Long Rifle (LR) calibre ammunition, and holds 25 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine.

The HK MP5 SD Semi-Automatic Rifle in .22 L.R. is manufactured exclusively by Walther under license from Heckler & Koch. It is the only genuine Heckler & Koch tactical rimfire replica available in the world. It includes the SD-style fore end, a retractable stock and pseudo-suppressor.

The standard "suppressor" is just a barrel-shroud - for looks. Shooting Stuff has developed a functional suppressor for this rifle. It is a simple drop-in part requiring no modifications to the firearm. Shooting Stuff has also developed a drop-in Picatinny rail for mounting an electro-optic sight.

name: Beretta A400 Xtreme S/A Shotgun 12ga  30"
description:
The Beretta A400 Xtreme Unico Synthetic 12ga Semi-Auto 30" Shotgun is a highly versatile semi-auto shotgun, chambered for 12 Gauge Shotgun calibre ammunition. This shotgun holds 3 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity magazine extensions are available (typically up to 12 + 1).

The Beretta A400 Xtreme is ideal for bird shooting, clay targets or 3-Gun action events. It reliably feeds every kind of 12-gauge shotshells, 70mm (2.75") to 89mm (3.5") long, loaded with anything from 24 gram to 64 gram of either steel or lead shot.

The black synthetic stock is adjustable for length of pull and features Beretta's Kick-off recoil management system and a Micro-Core butt-pad, making this a very soft-shooting shotgun.

The A400 action was developed with Beretta's "Blink" technology, making it one of the fastest cycling semi-auto shotguns on the market. Strong, yet light and compact, the vertical distance between your dominant eye and your supporting hand is minimised, thus increasing the chance of hitting the target. The top of the action features built-in rails, so it is easy to mount the optics of your choice; no gunsmithing required!

The 30" barrel is made of Steelium, Beretta's own steel blend, and incorporates OptimaBore HP interchangeable chokes.

The A400 Xtreme is easy to strip into just 5 components for maintenance.

Shooting Stuff has developed a range of magazine extension tubes for the Beretta A400. The modular Super-Lite is most popular!
short_description: The Beretta A400 Xtreme Unico Synthetic 12ga Semi-Auto 30" Shotgun is a highly versatile semi-auto shotgun, chambered for 12 Gauge Shotgun calibre ammunition. This shotgun holds 3 + 1  cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity magazine extensions are available (typically up to 12 + 1).

name: Beretta 1301 Comp 12ga Semi-Auto 24" Shotgun
description:
The Beretta 1301 Comp 12ga Semi-Auto 24" Shotgun is a competition-ready semi-auto shotgun, designed to win right out of the box. It is chambered for 12 Gauge Shotgun calibre ammunition. This shotgun holds 4 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity magazine extensions are available (typically up to 9 + 1, or more on request).

The Beretta 1301 Comp is ideal for 3-Gun action events, since it handles like a dream and has oversized controls. The cocking handle, bolt-release lever as well as the loading and ejection ports are oversized for simple and intuitive use under the heat of competition.

The 1301 Comp reliably feeds popular loads and will always perform like a Beretta!

The short, black-synthetic, tactical stock has aggressive, non-slip checkering for reliable handling, even under the stress of competition. The length of pull is adjustable.

The 1301 features Beretta's "Blink" gas operating system, making it one of the fastest cycling semi-auto shotguns on the market. Strong, yet light and compact, the vertical distance between your dominant eye and your supporting hand is minimised, thus increasing the chance of hitting the target. The top of the receiver is already drilled and tapped for rail mounts, so it is easy to mount the optics of your choice; no gunsmithing required!

The 24" barrel is made of Steelium, Beretta's own steel blend, and incorporates OptimaBore HP interchangeable chokes. The barrel features a wide, stepped, sporting rib with both a mid-bead and front fibre-optic sight for fast, instinctive shooting.

For those pushing their equipment to the extreme, the loading port on the Beretta 1301 Comp can be easily enlarged since the internal mechanisms are minimised, and kept to just the right side of the gun (in that area). Shooting Stuff has developed a range of magazine extension tubes for the Beretta 1301 Comp. The modular Super-Lite offer superior versatility, while the full-length Simplex Extension Tube is most popular!
short_description: The Beretta 1301 Comp 12ga Semi-Auto 24" Shotgun is a competition-ready semi-auto shotgun, designed to win right out of the box. It is chambered for 12 Gauge Shotgun calibre ammunition. This shotgun holds 4 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity magazine extensions are available (typically up to 9 + 1, or more on request).

name: Beretta CX4 Storm 9x19 Semi-Auto 16" Carbine
description:
The Beretta CX4 Storm 9x19 Semi-Auto 16" Carbine is a modern pistol-calibre carbine, chambered for 9mm Luger (9mm P, 9 x 19mm) calibre ammunition. This carbine / semi-auto rifle holds 17 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity magazines are available.

The Beretta CX4 Storm is a pistol-calibre, tactical carbine with pistol-Like controls, offering a familiar feel to those already used to modern Beretta combat handguns. The aperture and post sights are user-adjustable, and a full-length aluminium accessory rail makes it quick and easy to fit optical or red-dot sights.

The cold-forged 16" barrel offers superb accuracy, making this a great option for competitive 3-Gun shooting. The pistol-calibre makes it cheap to run, too!

The CX4 can be adapted to accept any full-size Beretta PX4, 90-series or 8000-series magazines, using optional adapters.

Left or right handed? No problem! The operating handle, safety and magazine release are reversible and case ejection can also be switched from right to left.

Tall or short? No problem! The length of pull is adjustable, making the Beretta CX4 a great fit for most shooters.

Need more accessories? The CX4 features a retractable Picatinny rail that extends from the fore-end, perfect for mounting tactical lights and other accessories. Additional rails can be mounted on the left, right or bottom; customisation deluxe!

The carbine is easy to take apart and reassemble, so cleaning after a day at the range is straightforward.
short_description: The Beretta CX4 Storm 9x19 Semi-Auto 16" Carbine is a modern pistol-calibre carbine, chambered for 9mm Luger (9mm P, 9 x 19mm) calibre ammunition. This carbine / semi-auto rifle holds 17 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity magazines are available.

name: ProArms PAR Mk3 .223 Rem Semi-Auto 12.5" Rifle
description:
The ProArms PAR Mk3 .223 Rem Semi-Auto 12.5" Rifle is a modern rendition of the proven AR-15 platform, chambered for 223 Remington calibre ammunition. This semi-auto rifle holds 30 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher and lower capacity magazines are available.

The PAR Mk3 semi-automatic rifle is manufactured in the Czech Republic by ProArms Armory. It has high-precision, CNC-machined parts, with far closer tolerances than parts made via standard production techniques. The frame and upper receiver are made from 7075-T6 aluminium alloy.

ProArms manufacturing quality guarantees a 100% interchangeability of parts, so replacing any worn or broken bits is easy! Furthermore, the rifle is manufactured to the American AR-15 production standard, ensuring compatibility with aftermarket parts and accessories.

The frame allows controls to be configured for left or right handed use. The forward-assist and case deflector have beed integrated into a slimmer, single block yet the overall weight of the rifle is maintained for added stability during rapid fire.

ProArms PAR Mk3 uses the cleaner gas-piston system, rather than the direct impingement gas system of the original AR-15 design. The PAR Mk3 has an adjustable gas block, with 4 settings, to reliably accomodate ammunition of different specifications. The entire piston system is designed for durability and maintenance-free operation.

A high quality 6-position telescopic stock is complemented by a modern-styled, ergonomic, beavertail pistol-grip (with integral spares compartment). The rigid, free-floating handguard incorporates four MIL-STD-1913 rails to fit a range of accessories from lights, lasers, optical sights, vertical grips, etc.

The PAR Mk3 barrels are exclusively produced by barrel specialist, Lothar Walther.

Sights are not included and must be purchased separately. MBUS-type, flip-up sights or any optical or electro-optical sights can be fitted to the top Picatinny rail.

This top-quality rifle has a 12.5" barrel with 1:7" twist.

name: Chiappa M1 9x19 Semi-Auto 18" Rifle
description:
The Chiappa M1 9x19 Semi-Auto 18" Rifle is a modern replica of the venerable M1 Carbine, chambered for 9mm Luger (9mm P, 9 x 19mm) calibre ammunition. This handgun holds 17 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity magazines are available.

The venerable M1 Carbine (a.k.a. U.S. Carbine, Caliber .30 M1) is a lightweight, easy to use semi-automatic rifle, originally chambered for the .30 Carbine cartridge. It became a standard _rearm for the American military during World War II, the Korean War and the early stages of the Vietnam War, and was widely used by USA and foreign military, paramilitary and police forces. In the post-war era it has also been a popular civilian _rearm for recreational use and collecting. Over 6.5-million M1 carbines of various models and variants were manufactured. Despite being designed by Winchester, most of these were made by other companies. The largest producer was the Inland division of General Motors, but the M1 Carbine was also made by contractors as diverse as IBM, the Underwood Typewriter Company, and the Rock-Ola jukebox company.

The Chiappa Firearmsí M1-series is a fine, modern replica of the M1 Carbine, featuring a blowback system and an adjustable rear sight. The M1 is available as the M1-9 in 9mm Luger, or as the M1-22 in .22 LR. Components are CNC-machined and are interchangeable with original M1 Carbine parts.

The M1-standard metal rear sight, adjustable in elevation and windage, can be removed to fit optical or electro-optical sights. The M1-standard metal front sight is fixed.

The bolt and the 18" barrel are made of matte, blued steel. The trigger guard and magazine guide are polymer.

A wooden stock version and a black synthetic stock version are available.

The magazine is compatible with the Beretta 92 pistol.

The rifle incorporates a standard M1 trigger block (safety catch).

This M1-9 semi-auto rifle has a wooden stock, and is chambered in 9mm Luger.
short_description: The Chiappa M1 9x19 Semi-Auto 18" Rifle is a modern replica of the venerable M1 Carbine, chambered for 9mm Luger (9mm P, 9 x 19mm) calibre ammunition. This handgun holds 17 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity magazines are available.

name: Steyr Mannlicher Luxus .270 Win Bolt Action 24" Rifle
description:
The Steyr Mannlicher Luxus .270 Win Bolt Action 24" Rifle is a premium grade hunting rifle, chambered in the popular, flat-shooting .270 Win calibre. It has a 4-round, detachable box magazine. The package includes a Swarovski Z6 2.5-15x44 P HD riflescope (already fitted), and four magazines.

The innovative Steyr Mannlicher Luxus is an elegant, modular concept for maximum flexibility. It can be configured as a light rifle for mountain hunting (Kudu in the Eastern Cape), or for hunting southern Africa's plains game in flat-shootng calibres (Springbuck in the Karoo) , through larger bushveld antelope like Kudu, up to the highest reliability for big-game hunting in Africa.

This pre-owned rifle is in excellent condition, practically like new.

name: Accuracy International AWM .338 Lapua Bolt Action Rifle
description:
The Accuracy International AWM .338 Lapua Bolt Action Rifle is the official sniper rifle of the British Army. This package includes the venerable Schmidt & Bender PM II 5-25x56 riflescope, already fitted to the rifle on an Accuracy International mount, as well as many accessories and ammunition. Although pre-owned, this package is brand new, unfired!

The Accuracy International AWM (Arctic Warfare Magnum) is a bolt-action sniper rifle manufactured by Accuracy International of Great Britain. The AWM is also unofficially referred to as the AWSM, or Arctic Warfare Super Magnum, denoting AWM rifles chambered in .338 Lapua Magnum.

Accuracy International recommends Schmidt & Bender PM II riflescopes for these rifles, with the 5-25x56 model being top of the range. Wikipedia offers additional information here.

We are selling this package for a client, so it is a one-time offering; just one package is available to the discerning long-range shooting enthusiast!

The seller is willing to consider reasonable offers, or a structured payment plan. The value of this package, should it be imported now, is estimated well over R300k!

name: Infinity IED Sight Tracker .40 S&W Competition Pistol
description:
The Infinity Firearms IED Sight Tracker .40 S&W; Semi-Auto 5.4"Competition Pistol is a custom-built, high-capacity, 1911-style pistol, chambered for 40 S&W; calibre ammunition. This handgun holds 17 + 1 cartridges using the extended magazines specifically designed for the IPSC Standard Gun division.

Infinity Fireams, based in Texas USA, builds the world's finest pistols based on the proven 1911-style platform. Every pistol is built to a customer's specific functional and cosmetic requirements, following design on Infinity's on-line Gunbuilder program. Shooting Stuff is available to help customers design their own Infinity, guiding them through the on-line process or by offering pistols ex-stock.

To ensure quality and strength, all parts are made in-house from billet barstock, and each pistol is hand-fit and finished with an extreme level of attention to detail - the slide cycles super-smoothly and the trigger is astounding - crisp and clean! Infinity's innovations are tried and tested by Team Infinity, over 40 of the top competitive shooters worldwide. All this ensures perfect reliability out of the box!

Some of the incredible Infinity innovations we've designed into our stock pistols, include:

  • Infinity mastered the metal grip to offer a wide selection of diameters, textures, lengths and trigger guard profiles that enable a near-perfect ergonomic fit to each shooter's hand. 
  • Infinity developed Accuracy Enhancing Technology (AET) that allows their firearms to deliver superb accuracy. Titanium Nitride (TiN) coated barrels feature gain twist rifling and the Sight Tracker adds an unported, hybrid-rib to the barrel where the front sight is mounted. In this way the front sight does not cycle back to front with the slide, it just moves up and down under recoil making it easier to track under recoil.
  • The Tri-Glide trigger system reduces contact points and friction, leading to the most sought-after trigger system for 1911 pistols! The interchangeable trigger inserts allow the trigger reach to be adjusted, as well as the "feel" - curved, flat and combinations are available.

Due to incredible international popularity of these fine pistols, Infinity Firearms has a production lead-time of 12 to 15 months. Shooting Stuff, the South African distributor for Infinity Firearms, has regular pre-booked slots to reduce this lead-time and offers several popular pistol designs ex-stock. By stocking spare parts, magazines, etc. and by using these fine firearms ourselves, Shooting Stuff with Infinity Firearms are able to support Infinity owners into the future, and beyond!

This Standard Gun is built on the Infinity Extended Dust-cover (IED) and features Infinity's Sight Tracker technology, with a serrated, steel front sight fitted to the ribbed barrel. The red Skater-Terrain grip tape fits snugly into the CNC-machined aluminium billet grip, yet is easily changed to give the pistol a fresh look!

Titanium Nitride (TiN) coated barrels feature gain twist rifling and the Sight Tracker adds an unported, hybrid-rib to the barrel where the front sight is mounted. In this way the front sight does not cycle back to front with the slide, it just moves up and down under recoil making it easier to track under recoil.
  • The Tri-Glide trigger system reduces contact points and friction, leading to the most sought-after trigger system for 1911 pistols! The interchangeable trigger inserts allow the trigger reach to be adjusted, as well as the "feel" - curved, flat and combinations are available.

Due to incredible international popularity of these fine pistols, Infinity Firearms has a production lead-time of 12 to 15 months. Shooting Stuff, the South African distributor for Infinity Firearms, has regular pre-booked slots to reduce this lead-time and offers several popular pistol designs ex-stock. By stocking spare parts, magazines, etc. and by using these fine firearms ourselves, Shooting Stuff with Infinity Firearms are able to support Infinity owners into the future, and beyond!

This Standard Gun is built on the Infinity Extended Dust-cover (IED) and features Infinity's Sight Tracker technology, with a 1mm, red fibre-optic front sight fitted to the ribbed barrel. The Micro-Pockets CNC-machined into the aluminium billet grip ensure a positive hold for best recoil control.

name: Dillon XL 650 Recommended Setup for 9mm Luger
description:
The Dillon XL 650 Recommended Setup for 9mm Luger is a progressive reloader capable of loading 800 to 1 000 rounds of 9mm ammunition per hour. Shooting Stuff has included the most popular options and safety features, all the things that make the XL 650 South Africa's favourite.

For complete peace of mind, the XL 650 is covered by Dillon’s legendary Lifetime "No-B.S." warranty. All electrical & electronic components in Dillon equipment are covered by a one-year warranty, as are textiles. Shooting Stuff fully supports Dillon’s warranty and has a spares cupboard with most spare parts available in stock. 

Click here to review a full description of the XL 650 and the many available options.
short_description: The Dillon XL 650 Recommended Setup for 9mm Luger is a progressive reloader capable of loading 800 to 1 000 rounds of 9mm ammunition per hour. Shooting Stuff has included the most popular options and safety features, all the things that make the XL 650 South Africa's favourite.
meta_title: Dillon XL 650 Recommended Setup for 9mm Luger | Reloading Presses | Shooting Stuff
meta_description: Looking for Dillon XL 650 Recommended Setup for 9mm Luger? Shooting Stuff has a large range of shooting products and accessories. Buy online today!
calibre_conversion:
Shooting Stuff has pre-configured this package for you for just one calibre, 9mm Luger. Your Dillon XL 650 can load many more calibres, and Calibre Conversion on the XL 650 is both as quick and easy as you want to make it. Dillon offers various levels of convenience to suit your requirements and budget. 

Option 1 - Minimum Kit 

As a minimum, you will need the following to change calibres:

  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
  • Reloading Die Set for the specific calibre.

Adding a Case Gauge for the specific calibre is always a good idea! 
Option 2 - Convenient Conversion

Option 1 does not take full advantage of the convenience offered by the XL 650's interchangeable tool head. So, if you want to leave your dies pre-set, you'll need:

  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
  • Reloading Die Set for the specific calibre.
  • Dillon XL 650 Tool Head (DLN-13863)

Including an additional Dillon Powder Die (DLN-20064) allows you to move your powder measure from tool head to tool head without changing the flare or belling adjustment. Consider taking a second powder die to also share the powder check system.

Depending on what calibre you are going to, and where you are changing from, you may also need a different case feed plate for the electric case feeder. Please refer to the calibre conversion chart in the Instruction Manual for the correct plate. The XL 650 Instruction Manual can be downloaded here, or call Shooting Stuff for advice. Available case feed plates (applicable to the XL 650) are:

  • Large pistol (DLN-21072)
  • Small pistol (DLN-21073)
  • Small rifle (DLN-21074)
  • Large rifle (DLN-21075)
  • Magnum rifle (DLN-18492)
We call this “calibre conversion, the moderately easy way” and believe that a case gauge for the specific calibre would be a good idea!
Option 3 - The Easy Way 

For the full Dillon convenience of changing calibres “the easy way” consider the option to leave your dies, powder system and powder check system set up and dedicated to a specific cartridge for faster, easier calibre changes. We call this “calibre conversion, the easy way”

  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
  • Reloading Die Set for the specific calibre.
  • The XL 650 Quick Change Kit (DLN-22059), which includes:
    • Powder measure (DLN-20782)
    • Powder die (DLN-20064)
    • Tool head (DLN-13863)
    • Tool head stand (DLN-22055)
  • Quick-change Dust Cover (DLN-11143) keeps the assembled tool head with powder measure dust free.
  • Case Gauge for the specific calibre (if available).

Depending on what calibre you are going to, and where you are changing from, you may also need a different case feed plate for the electric case feeder. Please refer to the calibre conversion chart in the Instruction Manual for the correct plate. The XL 650 Instruction Manual can be downloaded here, or call Shooting Stuff for advice. Available case feed plates (applicable to the XL 650) are:

  • Large pistol (DLN-21072)
  • Small pistol (DLN-21073)
  • Small rifle (DLN-21074)
  • Large rifle (DLN-21075)
  • Magnum rifle (DLN-18492)
key_features:
• The XL 650 is a 5-station, progressive reloading machine:
    • Station 1: Insert case into shell plate (at the bottom), resize and de-prime (at the top)
    • Station 2: Seat a new primer (at the bottom), and dispense propellant (at the top)
    • Station 3: Powder check (at the top)
    • Station 4: Seat the bullet (at the top)
    • Station 5: Crimp the cartridge case (at the top)
  • Insert cartridge cases automatically.
  • Index the shell plate automatically.
  • Feed and insert new primers automatically.
  • Dispense propellant automatically.
  • Check propellant level (for safety) in each and every case automatically.
  • Operator places bullets manually.
  • Eject loaded cartridges automatically.
  • Setup for 9mm Luger, but can load most popular handgun and rifle calibres (requires additional calibre-specific items).
  • Accepts standard ⅞” x 14 tpi (thread per inch) dies. 
  • Interchangeable tool head, for easy calibre conversion.
optional_accesories: Click here for a comprehensive list of optional accessories
package_contents:
Shooting Stuff's recommended XL 650 system comprises the following:

  • XL 650 Machine
 This is "the big white box" that includes the main reloading machine and 
  • Calibre Conversion Kit Box, with calibre-specific parts for 9mm Luger
  • Primer early warning system
  • Operating handle, with knob
  • Powder measure
  • 650 Primer System Parts Bag
  • 650 Accessory Box
  • Case feed mounting post and Case Feed Tube
  • Printed Instruction Manual
  • XL 650 Case Feeder
 220V electric case feeder with a small-pistol case feeder plate. True convenience!
  • Dillon 9mm Carbide Die Set

3-die set for progressive relaoding machines:

  • Carbide sizing die with decapping assembly
  • Bullet seating die
  • Separate taper crimp die
  • Powder Check System
 Once properly adjusted, this sensor verifies a safe charge in each and every case during the loading process.
  • Machine Mount
 Shooting Stuff's blue, powder coated machine mount raises the entire XL 650 above the bench's top, and spreads the load. A more stable system simply loads better! If necessary, the assembled 650-system stands securely on the machine mount.
  • Bullet Tray
 Dillon's cast Bullet Tray mounts to the left plate of the machine mount, and holds a few hundred bullets conveniently close to where they're needed.
  • Toolkit
 Shooting Stuff's Toolkit for the XL650 is a stylish, one-piece bracket that mounts to the "blue" Dillon progressive reloading machines to organise and store a set of ball-ended Allen wrenches and the 1-inch spanner. These tools are supplied in the kit and are what's required to adjust and basically service the machine.
  • Primer Flip Tray
  Dillon's metal flip tray is used to quickly get primers "the right way up" after dispensing these from their tray. 
  • Primer Pick-up Tubes
 A pack of 4 additional primer pick-up tubes used to pick-up small primers from the Flip Tray. Together with the one included with the reloading machine you'll be able to pre-fill 500 primers so that you can conveniently load a substantail batch of ammo with minimum interuption to replenish components.
  • Case lube
 While not absolutely essential when using carbide dies, we highly recommend Dillon's easy-to-apply, spray-on case lube. Trust us on this - you'll feel the difference!
  • DVD Instruction Manual
 Video conveys so much more than printed pictures and text. You won't find this info on YouTube!
  • Case Gauge
 Check each and every one of your 9mm cartridges for absolute confidence that none have high primers, none are cracked nor have other damage. If that sounds like too much effort just use the gauge occasionally to keep your reloading process in tune. Worth its weight in Stainless Steel!
  • Spare Parts Kit
 A collection of small parts that could easily get lost, or break, consider the Spare Parts Kit your insurance package until the Dillon Lifetime No-B.S. Warranty kicks in. After all, Murphy's Law states that if something can go wrong it will, and at the worst possible time (like the night before your match)
  • Setup

We will gladly setup your machine for you for FREE, as far as possible.

  • If you collect from us we can fully assemble the machine and included accessories, and then adjust the dies and powder charge.
  • If we ship the kit to you via courier, the extent of the setup is limited since we need to re-package the kit for safe shipping. We can install and adjust the dies, and set the powder charge, but you'll need to assemble all the bits.

 

Please make notes when checking out & finalising your purchase that include your load details, or send us an e-mail once your order is confirmed. If you want to assemble and setup everything yourself, learning the most about your machine, just omit the notes at check-out - simple!
recommended_accesories:
Primer Transfer 

Dillon offers a manual system of flip tray and pick-up tubes or an automated system to get the primers from their shipping box into the XL 650 primer magazine. While the manual approach is most popular - that's why they're included with this kit - the RF 100 is really convenient! Consider this a reminder ...

  • RF 100 Automatic Primer Filler 
 The Dillon RF 100 Automatic Primer Filler is an electrically powered machine to sort and transfer a hundred primers from their packaging box into a "transfer tube", for subsequent transfer into the primer magazine of your favourite Dillon progressive reloading machine. The RF 100 eliminates the need to manually fill primer pick-up tubes, and is available for either large or small primers with conversion kits to change to the other size.
  • RF 100 for large primers, 220V (DLN-97112)
  • Conversion kit to load small primers (DLN-17903)
  • RF 100 for small primers, 220V (DLN-97113)
  • Conversion kit to load large primers (DLN-17902)
required_accesories:
You will also need the following items (not included with this kit) to reload:

  • Scale 

Set and periodically check your powder charge, we recommend one of the following: 

  • Dillon D-Terminator electronic scale (DLN-10483), and protective case (CED-SCase)
  • Dillon Eliminator balance-beam scale (DLN-13480)
  • CED Universal digital pocket scale (CED-UDPS)
  • Loading Manual
  • RDM’s Somchem reloading manual, version 2 (SomchemManual) is the only manual to include data for local, South African propellants.
  • DVD: Competition Reloading with Brian Enos (DLN-14341) - a step-by-step guide through the reloading process for IPSC, Steel Challenge and other action-shooting styles.
  • Safety Glasses 

You should always protect your eyes when reloading. Primers contain explosive compounds and nitrocellulose propellant is extremely flammable, with explosive characteristics when burning in a confined volume. We recommend:

  • Draeger X-pect safety glasses (Xpect) are made of tough, clear polycarbonate for indoor use, like reloading.
  • Rudy Project Rydon glasses (Rydon) are made of super-tough ImpactX material for superior protection, while reloading or when shooting. 
  • Vernier calliper 

Set and check cartridge dimensions, like crimp and overall length, we recommend:

  • CED digital calliper (CED-DigiCal). The calliper is not absolutely essential, but close enough that we included it here!

Option 1 - Minimum Kit

Including an additional Dillon Powder Die (DLN-20064) allows you to move your powder measure from tool head to tool head without changing the flare or belling adjustment. Consider taking a second powder die to also share the powder check system.

,package_contents=

Shooting Stuff's recommended XL 650 system comprises the following:

  • XL 650 Machine
 This is "the big white box" that includes the main reloading machine and 
  • Calibre Conversion Kit Box, with calibre-specific parts for 9mm Luger
  • Primer early warning system
  • Operating handle, with knob
  • Powder measure
  • 650 Primer System Parts Bag
  • 650 Accessory Box
  • Case feed mounting post and Case Feed Tube
  • Printed Instruction Manual
  • XL 650 Case Feeder
 220V electric case feeder with a small-pistol case feeder plate. True convenience!
  • Dillon 9mm Carbide Die Set

3-die set for progressive relaoding machines:

  • Carbide sizing die with decapping assembly
  • Bullet seating die
  • Separate taper crimp die
  • Powder Check System
 Once properly adjusted, this sensor verifies a safe charge in each and every case during the loading process.
  • Machine Mount
 Shooting Stuff's blue, powder coated machine mount raises the entire XL 650 above the bench's top, and spreads the load. A more stable system simply loads better! If necessary, the assembled 650-system stands securely on the machine mount.
  • Bullet Tray
 Dillon's cast Bullet Tray mounts to the left plate of the machine mount, and holds a few hundred bullets conveniently close to where they're needed.
  • Toolkit
 Shooting Stuff's Toolkit for the XL650 is a stylish, one-piece bracket that mounts to the "blue" Dillon progressive reloading machines to organise and store a set of ball-ended Allen wrenches and the 1-inch spanner. These tools are supplied in the kit and are what's required to adjust and basically service the machine.
  • Primer Flip Tray
  Dillon's metal flip tray is used to quickly get primers "the right way up" after dispensing these from their tray. 
  • Primer Pick-up Tubes
 A pack of 4 additional primer pick-up tubes used to pick-up small primers from the Flip Tray. Together with the one included with the reloading machine you'll be able to pre-fill 500 primers so that you can conveniently load a substantail batch of ammo with minimum interuption to replenish components.
  • Case lube
 While not absolutely essential when using carbide dies, we highly recommend Dillon's easy-to-apply, spray-on case lube. Trust us on this - you'll feel the difference!
  • DVD Instruction Manual
 Video conveys so much more than printed pictures and text. You won't find this info on YouTube!
  • Case Gauge
 Check each and every one of your 9mm cartridges for absolute confidence that none have high primers, none are cracked nor have other damage. If that sounds like too much effort just use the gauge occasionally to keep your reloading process in tune. Worth its weight in Stainless Steel!
  • Spare Parts Kit
 A collection of small parts that could easily get lost, or break, consider the Spare Parts Kit your insurance package until the Dillon Lifetime No-B.S. Warranty kicks in. After all, Murphy's Law states that if something can go wrong it will, and at the worst possible time (like the night before your match)
  • Setup

We will gladly setup your machine for you for FREE, as far as possible.

  • If you collect from us we can fully assemble the machine and included accessories, and then adjust the dies and powder charge.
  • If we ship the kit to you via courier, the extent of the setup is limited since we need to re-package the kit for safe shipping. We can install and adjust the dies, and set the powder charge, but you'll need to assemble all the bits.

 

Please make notes when checking out & finalising your purchase that include your load details, or send us an e-mail once your order is confirmed. If you want to assemble and setup everything yourself, learning the most about your machine, just omit the notes at check-out - simple!
,product_weight=1,recommended_accesories=

Primer Transfer 

Dillon offers a manual system of flip tray and pick-up tubes or an automated system to get the primers from their shipping box into the XL 650 primer magazine. While the manual approach is most popular - that's why they're included with this kit - the RF 100 is really convenient! Consider this a reminder ...

  • RF 100 Automatic Primer Filler 
 The Dillon RF 100 Automatic Primer Filler is an electrically powered machine to sort and transfer a hundred primers from their packaging box into a "transfer tube", for subsequent transfer into the primer magazine of your favourite Dillon progressive reloading machine. The RF 100 eliminates the need to manually fill primer pick-up tubes, and is available for either large or small primers with conversion kits to change to the other size.
  • RF 100 for large primers, 220V (DLN-97112)
  • Conversion kit to load small primers (DLN-17903)
  • RF 100 for small primers, 220V (DLN-97113)
  • Conversion kit to load large primers (DLN-17902)

brand=Dillon Precision,calibre_conversion=

Shooting Stuff has pre-configured this package for you for just one calibre, 9mm Luger. Your Dillon XL 650 can load many more calibres, and Calibre Conversion on the XL 650 is both as quick and easy as you want to make it. Dillon offers various levels of convenience to suit your requirements and budget. 

Option 1 - Minimum Kit 

As a minimum, you will need the following to change calibres:

  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
  • Reloading Die Set for the specific calibre.

Adding a Case Gauge for the specific calibre is always a good idea! 
Option 2 - Convenient Conversion

Option 1 does not take full advantage of the convenience offered by the XL 650's interchangeable tool head. So, if you want to leave your dies pre-set, you'll need:

  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
  • Reloading Die Set for the specific calibre.
  • Dillon XL 650 Tool Head (DLN-13863)

Including an additional Dillon Powder Die (DLN-20064) allows you to move your powder measure from tool head to tool head without changing the flare or belling adjustment. Consider taking a second powder die to also share the powder check system.

Depending on what calibre you are going to, and where you are changing from, you may also need a different case feed plate for the electric case feeder. Please refer to the calibre conversion chart in the Instruction Manual for the correct plate. The XL 650 Instruction Manual can be downloaded here, or call Shooting Stuff for advice. Available case feed plates (applicable to the XL 650) are:

  • Large pistol (DLN-21072)
  • Small pistol (DLN-21073)
  • Small rifle (DLN-21074)
  • Large rifle (DLN-21075)
  • Magnum rifle (DLN-18492)
We call this “calibre conversion, the moderately easy way” and believe that a case gauge for the specific calibre would be a good idea!
Option 3 - The Easy Way 

For the full Dillon convenience of changing calibres “the easy way” consider the option to leave your dies, powder system and powder check system set up and dedicated to a specific cartridge for faster, easier calibre changes. We call this “calibre conversion, the easy way”

  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
  • Reloading Die Set for the specific calibre.
  • The XL 650 Quick Change Kit (DLN-22059), which includes:
    • Powder measure (DLN-20782)
    • Powder die (DLN-20064)
    • Tool head (DLN-13863)
    • Tool head stand (DLN-22055)
  • Quick-change Dust Cover (DLN-11143) keeps the assembled tool head with powder measure dust free.
  • Case Gauge for the specific calibre (if available).

Depending on what calibre you are going to, and where you are changing from, you may also need a different case feed plate for the electric case feeder. Please refer to the calibre conversion chart in the Instruction Manual for the correct plate. The XL 650 Instruction Manual can be downloaded here, or call Shooting Stuff for advice. Available case feed plates (applicable to the XL 650) are:

  • Large pistol (DLN-21072)
  • Small pistol (DLN-21073)
  • Small rifle (DLN-21074)
  • Large rifle (DLN-21075)
  • Magnum rifle (DLN-18492)
,display_weight=28.2,has_tiers=No,is_recurring=No,key_features=
  • The XL 650 is a 5-station, progressive reloading machine:
    • Station 1: Insert case into shell plate (at the bottom), resize and de-prime (at the top)
    • Station 2: Seat a new primer (at the bottom), and dispense propellant (at the top)
    • Station 3: Powder check (at the top) - requires an additional sensor
    • Station 4: Seat the bullet (at the top)
    • Station 5: Crimp the cartridge case (at the top)
  • Insert cartridge cases automatically.
  • Index the shell plate automatically.
  • Feed and insert new primers automatically.
  • Dispense propellant automatically.
  • Check propellant level (for safety) in each and every case automatically - requires an additional Powder Check sensor.
  • Operator places bullets manually.
  • Eject loaded cartridges automatically.
  • Setup for 9mm Luger, but can load most popular handgun and rifle calibres (requires additional calibre-specific items).
  • Accepts standard ⅞” x 14 tpi (thread per inch) dies. 
  • Interchangeable tool head, for easy calibre conversion.

Shooting Stuff's Sensible Minimum Setup for XL 650 system comprises the following:

  • XL 650 Machine
 This is "the big white box" that includes the main reloading machine and 
  • Calibre Conversion Kit Box, with calibre-specific parts for 9mm Luger
  • Primer early warning system
  • Operating handle, with knob
  • Powder measure
  • 650 Primer System Parts Bag
  • 650 Accessory Box
  • Case feed mounting post and Case Feed Tube
  • Printed Instruction Manual
  • Dillon 9mm Carbide Die Set

3-die set for progressive relaoding machines:

  • Carbide sizing die with decapping assembly
  • Bullet seating die
  • Separate taper crimp die
  • 1" Spanner
 Shooting Stuff's 1-inch spanner gets in to the small space available on the tool head so that you can adjust the dies as required. Conventional spanners and shifters are just too bulky!
  • Primer Flip Tray
 Dillon's metal flip tray is used to quickly get primers "the right way up" after dispensing these from their tray. 
  • Case lube
 While not absolutely essential when using carbide dies, we highly recommend Dillon's easy-to-apply, spray-on case lube. Trust us on this - you'll feel the difference!
  • Case Gauge
 Check each and every one of your 9mm cartridges for absolute confidence that none have high primers, none are cracked nor have other damage. If that sounds like too much effort just use the gauge occasionally to keep your reloading process in tune. Worth its weight in Stainless Steel!
  • Setup

We will gladly setup your machine for you for FREE, as far as possible.

  • If you collect from us we can fully assemble the machine and included accessories, and then adjust the dies and powder charge.
  • If we ship the kit to you via courier, the extent of the setup is limited since we need to re-package the kit for safe shipping. We can install and adjust the dies, and set the powder charge, but you'll need to assemble all the bits.

 

Please make notes when checking out & finalising your purchase that include your load details, or send us an e-mail once your order is confirmed. If you want to assemble and setup everything yourself, learning the most about your machine, just omit the notes at check-out - simple!

You will also need the following items (not included with this kit) to reload:

  • Scale 

Set and periodically check your powder charge, we recommend one of the following: 

  • Dillon D-Terminator electronic scale (DLN-10483), and protective case (CED-SCase)
  • Dillon Eliminator balance-beam scale (DLN-13480)
  • CED Universal digital pocket scale (CED-UDPS)
  • Loading Manual
  • RDM’s Somchem reloading manual, version 2 (SomchemManual) is the only manual to include data for local, South African propellants.
  • DVD: Competition Reloading with Brian Enos (DLN-14341) - a step-by-step guide through the reloading process for IPSC, Steel Challenge and other action-shooting styles.
  • Safety Glasses 

You should always protect your eyes when reloading. Primers contain explosive compounds and nitrocellulose propellant is extremely flammable, with explosive characteristics when burning in a confined volume. We recommend:

  • Draeger X-pect safety glasses (Xpect) are made of tough, clear polycarbonate for indoor use, like reloading.
  • Rudy Project Rydon glasses (Rydon) are made of super-tough ImpactX material for superior protection, while reloading or when shooting. 
  • Vernier calliper 

Set and check cartridge dimensions, like crimp and overall length, we recommend:

  • CED digital calliper (CED-DigiCal). The calliper is not absolutely essential, but close enough that we included it here!

name: CZ 75 TS 9x19 Competition Pistol (Orange)
description:
The CZ 75 TS (Tactical Sport) 9x19 Competition Pistol (Orange) is a modern competition firearm with a traditional steel frame, chambered for 9mm Luger calibre ammunition. This handgun holds 20 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity magazines are available.

The CZ 75 TS (Tactical Sports) is a locked breech pistol, designed for sport shooting. It is offered in two fundamental variants, for IPSC Standard Gun division and for IPSC Open Gun division.

Based on the proven CZ 75 heritage, the TS is bigger with a full dust cover (the frame ahead of the trigger guard), and differs from the original CZ 75 in having only a single action trigger mechanism. The match trigger is adjustable.

The magazine catch is extended for easier operation and the bottom of the grip includes an integral magazine well for easier and quicker reloads.

The CZ 75 TS-9 Orange has a 1.5mm red fibre-optic front sight, plain black Novak-style rear sight. This competition pistol features an ergonomic manual safety catch, but is without a firing pin safety for an improved trigger pull. This distinctive Orange model has bright orange anodised aluminium grip panels, as well as matching magazine base pads. The Orange offers enhanced accuracy through the hand fitted, polished barrel mated to a precisely fitted slide with minimum lateral tolerances. The improved single-action trigger mechanism with re-designed hammer further enhances delivered precision.

name: CED 7000 Shot Activated Timer Bundle
description:
CED 7000 Shot Timer Bundle - with a silicone skin in your colour choice, Rotating Belt Clip and a Retractable Lanyard Set.

The CED 7000 Shot Timer is compact, easy to operate, full featured timer features custom PAR for single or multiple time settings, variable delay intervals to .01 seconds, an easy-to-read illuminated display countdown mode and auxiliary jack for external loud horn, visual starts or target turning! 

The timer has a 999.99 second time record capacity and can be upgraded for wireless connection to a CED BigBoard or Time Keeper for displaying results more than 40 meters away from the timer.

name: SIG Sauer R522 Commando .22 LR Semi-auto 16" Rifle
description:
The SIG Sauer R522 Commando .22 LR Semi-auto 16" Rifle is a modern firearm, chambered for .22 LR calibre (rimfire) ammunition. This rifle holds 25 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; lower capacity magazines are available.

This is a modern semi-auto rifle, ideal for 3-Gun and training. It features a Picatinny rail on the receiver, for mounting optional optical sights.

The Commando features an inert training suppressor mounted by standard ½" x 28 tpi. The inert tactical trainer can easily be removed and a functional suppressor fitted.

name: Glock G19 Gen 4 MOS 9x19 Compact Pistol
description:
The Glock G19 Gen 4 MOS 9x19 Compact Pistol is a modern firearm with a lightweight polymer frame, chambered for 9mm Luger (9mm P, 9 x 19mm) calibre ammunition. This fourth generation handgun holds 15 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity magazines are available. The MOS-models are designed to accept ruggedised Miniature Optical Sights, mounted to the slide.

Glock Safe-Action pistols were introduced in the 1980's and have excelled in military, police and civilian environments. The Glock was the first commercially successful polymer framed handgun. Initially offered in 9x19mm Glock pistols are now available in many other calibres too.

With several different sizes available, there is a Glock to suit almost any requirement. Long-slide models are great for competition, standard models are well suited for officers on duty, for example, and the compact, sub-compact or slimline models offer a balanced, self-defence capability. Their versatility ensures that most models are multi-functional, serving well for home defence, daily carry, duty or competition!

The polymer frame and grip is tough, lightweight and corrosion resistant. Tenifer, the 'nearly hard as diamond' Glock surface treatment, protects the barrel and slide while remaining anti-reflective.

Shooting Stuff recommends Glock pistols! With minimal external controls they are extremely easy to use and to learn to use, for left-handed and right-handed shooters! They are reliable, durable and lightweight. Three independent, automatic safety features ensure that the pistol fires when, and only when, the trigger is deliberately pulled. All three safety features re-engage when the trigger is released, automatically securing the pistol again. We believe that Glock is the best supported firearms brand in South Africa, with spares, magazines, holsters and many aftermarket accessories available ex-stock.

Three automatic safety features:

  1. The trigger safety prevents inadvertent firing by lateral force on the trigger, and is automatically depressed when initial tension is applied to the trigger. It automatically resets when the trigger is released.
  • The firing pin safety is a hardened steel plunger that blocks the firing pin from igniting the chambered cartridge until the trigger is pulled to the rear, pushing the firing pin safety up and out of the way. It automatically reactivates when the trigger is released.
  • The drop safety prevents the trigger mechanism from "activating" and firing an unintentional shot in the event that the pistol drops or falls onto a hard surface. Only with sufficient rearward travel of the trigger can the firing pin be released, firing the shot.

    • The extractor serves as a loaded chamber indicator, and the trigger offers further visual and tactile cues to the gun's status.

    Compact models are most versatile, offering a great balance between open carry, concealed carry and range use. The integrated mounting rail allows quick and convenient mounting / dismounting of accessories like tactical torches and lasers.

name: CED M2 Chronograph Bundle
description:
The Blue Mondy Special includes the CED M2 Chronograph and a Shooting Stuff Chrono Bag.

The CED M2 Chronograph is an update to the CED Millennium Chronograph which has been an industry standard for the past eight years! The M2 has double the operating speed of its predecessor, incorporating a micro-controller that runs at 48 MHz, it expands the operation range from 50 fps to 7,000 fps. The storage capacity of this model has also been expanded, enabling storage of over 1000 stored velocities!

With the expanded digital chip design, the M2 can read velocities at much lower light levels, from early morning till almost sunset! In addition to all the improvements, the M2 also has a USB interface, making it easier than ever to download and save your data to your PC using the CED Data Collector Software.

name: Dillon Large Case Cleaning Bundle
description:
The Large Case Cleaning Bundle includes the Dillon CV 2001 Case Cleaner, CM 2000 Large Case/Media Separator, Rapid Polish and case cleaning media.

The Dillon CV 2001 Case Cleaner is the largest vibratory case cleaner in the industry, with a capacity for around 1 500 9mmP cases, or 550 .30-06 cases. Add a little Rapid Polish to your cleaning media and this tumbler will clean your brass shiny-bright in an hour and a half! The internally cooled, thermally protected motor is powerful enough to drive the 6kg load.

The bowl and base are both made from 5.5mm thick, injection moulded high strength polypropylene. You will require case cleaning media. We use crushed Peach Pip Media for cleaning dirty brass, and Corn Cob for a final polish! 

Also included in the bundle is the CM 2000 Case Media Separator to conveniently separate the cases from the media. 

All the electrical & electronic components of Dillon equipment are covered by a one-year warranty from date of purchase. This unit has a 1-year warranty.
short_description: The Dillon CM 2000 Large Case/Media Separator is a rotating squirrel-cage over a 18" x 22"  media collection tub, that conveniently separates the cleaned cartridge cases from the cleaning media after these have been processed in Dillon's CV 2001 vibratory case cleaner.

name: CZ Shadow 2 9x19 Comp Pistol (black, blue grips)
description:
The CZ Shadow 2 9x19 Competition Pistol (Black with blue grips) is a modern competition firearm with a traditional steel frame, chambered for 9mm Luger (9mm P, 9 x 19mm) calibre ammunition. This handgun holds 18 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity magazines are available.

CZ designers set out to improve the CZ 75 SP-01 Shadow in terms of speed, accuracy and durability. The CZ Shadow 2 was the result - an affordable sport pistol that is perfectly suited for IPSC Production Division. 

Speed improvement was addressed by modernising principal parts of the pistol. The CZ Shadow 2 frame design improved the alignment between the shooter's hand and the barrel axis, to reduce the perceived recoil. The heavier frame and increased weight in the front part of the slide reduce the recoil. The cocking grooves in the front and rear of the slide, and the checkering on the frame and anodized Aluminium grips enhance the contact between gun and hand. The CZ Shadow 2 has a very smooth trigger action and a shortened trigger reset. These aspects all contribute to increased shooting speed.

The extended 125 mm barrel and the new longer height-adjustble sights contribute to the improved accuracy of the CZ Shadow 2.

The CZ Shadow 2 has an Arcor finish for high wear and corrosion resistance, making it extremely durable.
short_description: The CZ Shadow 2 9x19 Competition Pistol (Black with blue grips) is a modern competition firearm with a traditional steel frame, chambered for 9mm Luger (9mm P, 9 x 19mm) calibre ammunition. This handgun holds 18 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity magazines are available.

name: Dillon Steel Rifle 3-die set
description:
The Dillon Steel Rifle die set includes a sizing/depriming die, a bullet seating die and a crimp die.

Dillon dies are designed to work best on Dillon progressive reloading machines. All Dillon dies have standard 7/8"x14tpi threads and the rifle calibre sizing/depriming die has an intergral stuck-case remover designed in!

The new 1" lock rings allow a little more space on the tool head (when adjusting  the dies) for the 1" wrench to fit.

Case lube is required for steel rifle dies (we recommend Dillon case lube).
short_description: The Dillon Steel Rifle 3-die set includes a sizing/depriming die, a bullet seating die and a crimp die in the chosen calibre.

All Dillon dies are hex-headed for easy adjustment using a wrench.

Sizing Die :

  • Full-length steel die with radiussed opening, to work best on progressive reloaders!
  • Polished to a high micro-finish

  • Carbide expander ball for effortless neck expansion
  • Decapping assembly serves as stuck case remover, if required

Bullet seating die:

  • Generously radiussed die mouth for smooth progressive reloading

Crimp die :

  • Precise, uniform taper crimp
