name: Dillon Carbide Handgun 3-die set
description:
The Dillon Carbide Handgun 3-die set includes a sizing/depriming die, a bullet seating die and a crimp die.

Dillon dies are designed to work best on Dillon progressive reloading machines. Although all Dillon dies have standard 7/8"x14tpi threads, the handgun die sets do not include an expander die as this function occurs in the powder dispensing station; the calibre-specific powder funnel is part of the calibre conversion kit.

The new 1" lock rings allow a little more space on the tool head (when adjusting  the dies) for the 1" wrench to fit.

We recommend using Dillon case lube even on carbide pistol dies; you'll feel the significant reduction in force required to operate the machine.

name: Dillon Carbide Case Trim Die
description:
The Dillon Case Trim Die is designed to resize and, when used together with the Dillon RT1500 or RT1200B electric case trimmers, to also trim the cartridge case to the correct length.

This carbide die is caliber-specific.

Brass chips / shavings are drawn off through a vacuum manifold that clamps to the outside of the die. The vacuum manifold is supplied separately as part of the electric case trimmer assembly.

name: Dillon Steel Rifle Sizing die
description:
The Dillon Steel Rifle Sizing die offers full-length sizing, to minimum tolerances, sizing cases down to function in self-loading rifles. The depriming assembly includes a carbide expander ball for neck expansion, and also functions as a built-in stuck case remover.

Dillon dies are designed to work best on Dillon progressive reloading machines. All Dillon dies have standard 7/8"x14tpi threads and the sizing/depriming die has an intergral stuck-case remover designed in!

The new 1" lock rings allow a little more space on the tool head (when adjusting  the dies) for the 1" wrench to fit.

Case lube is required for all rifle dies, steel or carbide, and we recommend Dillon case lube.

name: Dillon Carbide Rifle Sizing die
description:
The Dillon Carbide Rifle Sizing die offers full-length sizing, to minimum tolerances, sizing cases down to function in self-loading rifles. The depriming assembly includes a carbide expander ball for neck expansion, and also functions as a built-in stuck case remover.

Dillon dies are designed to work best on Dillon progressive reloading machines. All Dillon dies have standard 7/8"x14tpi threads and the sizing/depriming die has an intergral stuck-case remover designed in!

The new 1" lock rings allow a little more space on the tool head (when adjusting  the dies) for the 1" wrench to fit.

Case lube is required for all rifle dies, steel or carbide, and we recommend Dillon case lube.

name: Dillon Steel Rifle Crimp die
description:
The Dillon Steel Rifle Crimp die is a taper crimp die specially configured to centre both the case neck and the case body, aligning the cartridge for a more uniform crimp. A taper crimp is recommended for ammunition intended to be used in semi-auto and lever-action rifles.

Dillon dies are designed to work best on Dillon progressive reloading machines. All Dillon dies have standard 7/8"x14tpi threads.

The new 1" lock rings allow a little more space on the tool head (when adjusting  the dies) for the 1" wrench to fit.

The case gauge is essential for long case life, especially with semi-automatic firearms!

name: Redding Titanium Carbide 3-Die Set-32 Auto (ACP)
description:
The Redding Titanium Carbide 3-Die Set - 32 ACP is a set of three conventional dies for reloading handgun ammunition. The sizing die is fitted with a ring of Titanium Carbide, the ideal material for resizing cartridge cases.

Titanium Carbide has the highest hardness of any readily available carbide, and has a slippery non-galling surface that is ideal for resizing of cartridge cases without requiring lubricant. While not required, we still recommend using an easy-to-apply case lubricant like Dillon DCL, with lanolin (part number DLN-13733). This saves wear and tear on the cartridge cases and your reloading equipment; you'll feel the significant reduction in force required to operate the press!

Although this conventional die set can be used universally, it is intended for non-progressive reloading machines.
This set includes three dies; a titanium carbide sizing die, expander die and bullet seating die with built-in crimp.

These dies can be used to load 32 Auto (ACP) ammunition and similar calibres, where applicable. See the Technical Specs tab for more details on compatible calibres.

name: Redding Titanium Carbide 3-Die Set-380 Auto (ACP)
description:
The Redding Titanium Carbide 3-Die Set - 32 ACP is a set of three conventional dies for reloading handgun ammunition. The sizing die is fitted with a ring of Titanium Carbide, the ideal material for resizing cartridge cases.

Titanium Carbide has the highest hardness of any readily available carbide, and has a slippery non-galling surface that is ideal for resizing of cartridge cases without requiring lubricant. While not required, we still recommend using an easy-to-apply case lubricant like Dillon DCL, with lanolin (part number DLN-13733). This saves wear and tear on the cartridge cases and your reloading equipment; you'll feel the significant reduction in force required to operate the press!

Although this conventional die set can be used universally, it is intended for non-progressive reloading machines.
This set includes three dies; a titanium carbide sizing die, expander die and bullet seating die with built-in crimp.

These dies can be used to load 32 Auto (ACP) ammunition and similar calibres, where applicable. See the Technical Specs tab for more details on compatible calibres.

name: Dillon Locator Pin #2
short_description:
The Dillon Locator Pin #2 is a small brass pin that correctly positions the cartridge case in the shell plate. Each combination of shell plate and locator pin size is unique for a range of similar calibres. The locator pins are included with each calibre conversion kit.

Consult the manual for your Dillon progressive reloading machine to determine the correct pin for your needs. Most of the Dillon machines require three pins, but the 1050 requires six.

name: Dillon XL 650 Comprehensive Setup for 9mm Luger
description:
The Dillon XL 650 Comprehensive Setup for 9mm Luger is a progressive reloader capable of loading 800 to 1 000 rounds of 9mm ammunition per hour. Shooting Stuff has included all the options and safety features, all the things that make the XL 650 South Africa's favourite. Barring the autodrive and bullet feeder, this is the "Full Monty"!

For complete peace of mind, the XL 650 is covered by Dillon’s legendary Lifetime "No-B.S." warranty. All electrical & electronic components in Dillon equipment are covered by a one-year warranty, as are textiles. Shooting Stuff fully supports Dillon’s warranty and has a spares cupboard with most spare parts available in stock. 

Click here to review a full description of the XL 650 and the many available options.

meta_description: Looking for Dillon XL 650 Comprehensive Setup for 9mm Luger? Shooting Stuff has a large range of shooting products and accessories. Buy online today!
calibre_conversion:
Shooting Stuff has pre-configured this package for you for just one calibre, 9mm Luger. Your Dillon XL 650 can load many more calibres, and Calibre Conversion on the XL 650 is both as quick and easy as you want to make it. Dillon offers various levels of convenience to suit your requirements and budget. 

Option 1 - Minimum Kit 

As a minimum, you will need the following to change calibres:

  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
  • Reloading Die Set for the specific calibre.

Adding a Case Gauge for the specific calibre is always a good idea! 
Option 2 - Convenient Conversion

Option 1 does not take full advantage of the convenience offered by the XL 650's interchangeable tool head. So, if you want to leave your dies pre-set, you'll need:

  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
  • Reloading Die Set for the specific calibre.
  • Dillon XL 650 Tool Head (DLN-13863)

Including an additional Dillon Powder Die (DLN-20064) allows you to move your powder measure from tool head to tool head without changing the flare or belling adjustment. Consider taking a second powder die to also share the powder check system.

Depending on what calibre you are going to, and where you are changing from, you may also need a different case feed plate for the electric case feeder. Please refer to the calibre conversion chart in the Instruction Manual for the correct plate. The XL 650 Instruction Manual can be downloaded here, or call Shooting Stuff for advice. Available case feed plates (applicable to the XL 650) are:

  • Large pistol (DLN-21072)
  • Small pistol (DLN-21073)
  • Small rifle (DLN-21074)
  • Large rifle (DLN-21075)
  • Magnum rifle (DLN-18492)
We call this “calibre conversion, the moderately easy way” and believe that a case gauge for the specific calibre would be a good idea!
Option 3 - The Easy Way 

For the full Dillon convenience of changing calibres “the easy way” consider the option to leave your dies, powder system and powder check system set up and dedicated to a specific cartridge for faster, easier calibre changes. We call this “calibre conversion, the easy way”

  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
  • Reloading Die Set for the specific calibre.
  • The XL 650 Quick Change Kit (DLN-22059), which includes:
    • Powder measure (DLN-20782)
    • Powder die (DLN-20064)
    • Tool head (DLN-13863)
    • Tool head stand (DLN-22055)
  • Quick-change Dust Cover (DLN-11143) keeps the assembled tool head with powder measure dust free.
  • Case Gauge for the specific calibre (if available).

Depending on what calibre you are going to, and where you are changing from, you may also need a different case feed plate for the electric case feeder. Please refer to the calibre conversion chart in the Instruction Manual for the correct plate. The XL 650 Instruction Manual can be downloaded here, or call Shooting Stuff for advice. Available case feed plates (applicable to the XL 650) are:

  • Large pistol (DLN-21072)
  • Small pistol (DLN-21073)
  • Small rifle (DLN-21074)
  • Large rifle (DLN-21075)
  • Magnum rifle (DLN-18492)
key_features:
• The XL 650 is a 5-station, progressive reloading machine:
    • Station 1: Insert case into shell plate (at the bottom), resize and de-prime (at the top)
    • Station 2: Seat a new primer (at the bottom), and dispense propellant (at the top)
    • Station 3: Powder check (at the top)
    • Station 4: Seat the bullet (at the top)
    • Station 5: Crimp the cartridge case (at the top)
  • Insert cartridge cases automatically.
  • Index the shell plate automatically.
  • Feed and insert new primers automatically.
  • Dispense propellant automatically.
  • Check propellant level (for safety) in each and every case automatically.
  • Operator places bullets manually.
  • Eject loaded cartridges automatically.
  • Setup for 9mm Luger, but can load most popular handgun and rifle calibres (requires additional calibre-specific items).
  • Accepts standard ⅞” x 14 tpi (thread per inch) dies. 
  • Interchangeable tool head, for easy calibre conversion.
optional_accesories: Click here for a comprehensive list of optional accessories
package_contents:
Shooting Stuff's comprehensive XL 650 system comprises the following:

  • XL 650 Machine
 This is "the big white box" that includes the main reloading machine and 
  • Calibre Conversion Kit Box, with calibre-specific parts for 9mm Luger
  • Primer early warning system
  • Operating handle, with knob
  • Powder measure
  • 650 Primer System Parts Bag
  • 650 Accessory Box
  • Case feed mounting post and Case Feed Tube
  • Printed Instruction Manual
  • XL 650 Case Feeder
 220V electric case feeder with a small-pistol case feeder plate. True convenience!
  • Dillon 9mm Carbide Die Set

3-die set for progressive reloading machines:

  • Carbide sizing die with decapping assembly
  • Bullet seating die
  • Separate taper crimp die
  • Low Powder Sensor
 This is a warning system that provides an audible and visual reminder when it's time to refill your powder reservoir.
  • Powder Checks System
 Once properly adjusted, this sensor verifies a safe charge in each and every case during the loading process.
  • Machine Mount
 Shooting Stuff's blue, powder coated machine mount raises the entire XL 650 above the bench's top, and spreads the load. A more stable system simply loads better! If necessary, the assembled 650-system stands securely on the machine mount.
  • Bullet Tray
 Dillon's cast Bullet Tray mounts to the left plate of the machine mount, and holds a few hundred bullets conveniently close to where they're needed.
  • Toolkit
 Shooting Stuff's Toolkit for the XL650 is a stylish, one-piece bracket that mounts to the "blue" Dillon progressive reloading machines to organise and store a set of ball-ended Allen wrenches and the 1-inch spanner. These tools are supplied in the kit and are what's required to adjust and basically service the machine.
  • Smooth-glide Roller Handle
 Shooting Stuff's roller handle runs on sealed bearings for enhanced reloading comfort and tactile feedback when seating primers.
  • No-Spill Primer kit
 The Shooting Stuff NoSpill Primer Kit for XL650 is an upgrade to the Dillon XL 650 progressive reloading machine that ensures all spent primers and any unused live primers are captured and retained during the loading process.
  • XL650 Machine Cover
 The Shooting Stuff XL 650 Machine Cover is perfect for keeping your equipment clean and free of dust, when not in use.This cover is suitable for the Dillon XL 650, Super 1050 and SL900 progressive reloading machines.
  • Primer Flip Tray
 Dillon's metal flip tray is used to quickly get primers "the right way up" after dispensing these from their tray. 
  • Primer Pick-up Tubes
 A pack of 4 additional primer pick-up tubes used to pick-up small primers from the Flip Tray. Together with the one included with the reloading machine you'll be able to pre-fill 500 primers so that you can conveniently load a substantail batch of ammo with minimum interuption to replenish components.
  • Case lube
 While not absolutely essential when using carbide dies, we highly recommend Dillon's easy-to-apply, spray-on case lube. Trust us on this - you'll feel the difference!
  • Case Gauge
 Check each and every one of your cartridges for absolute confidence that none have high primers, none are cracked nor have other damage. If that sounds like too much effort just use the gauge occasionally to keep your reloading process in tune. Worth its weight in Stainless Steel!
  • Spare Parts Kit
 A collection of small parts that could easily get lost, or break, consider the Spare Parts Kit your insurance package until the Dillon Lifetime No-B.S. Warranty kicks in. After all, Murphy's Law states that if something can go wrong it will, and at the worst possible time (like the night before your match)
  • Setup

We will gladly setup your machine for you for FREE, as far as possible.

  • If you collect from us we can fully assemble the machine and included accessories, and then adjust the dies and powder charge.
  • If we ship the kit to you via courier, the extent of the setup is limited since we need to re-package the kit for safe shipping. We can install and adjust the dies, and set the powder charge, but you'll need to assemble all the bits.

Please add notes when checking out & finalising your purchase that include your load details, or send us an e-mail once your order is confirmed. If you want to assemble and setup everything yourself, learning the most about your machine, just omit the notes at check-out - simple!
recommended_accesories:
Primer Transfer 

Dillon offers a manual system of flip tray and pick-up tubes or an automated system to get the primers from their shipping box into the XL 650 primer magazine. While the manual approach is most popular - that's why they're included with this kit - the RF 100 is really convenient! Consider this a reminder ...

  • RF 100 Automatic Primer Filler 
 The Dillon RF 100 Automatic Primer Filler is an electrically powered machine to sort and transfer a hundred primers from their packaging box into a "transfer tube", for subsequent transfer into the primer magazine of your favourite Dillon progressive reloading machine. The RF 100 eliminates the need to manually fill primer pick-up tubes, and is available for either large or small primers with conversion kits to change to the other size.
  • RF 100 for large primers, 220V (DLN-97112)
  • Conversion kit to load small primers (DLN-17903)
  • RF 100 for small primers, 220V (DLN-97113)
  • Conversion kit to load large primers (DLN-17902)
required_accesories:
You will also need the following items (not included with this kit) to reload:

  • Scale 

Set and periodically check your powder charge, we recommend one of the following: 

  • Dillon D-Terminator electronic scale (DLN-10483), and protective case (CED-SCase)
  • Dillon Eliminator balance-beam scale (DLN-13480)
  • CED Universal digital pocket scale (CED-UDPS)
  • Loading Manual
  • RDM’s Somchem reloading manual, version 2 (SomchemManual) is the only manual to include data for local, South African propellants.
  • DVD: Competition Reloading with Brian Enos (DLN-14341) - a step-by-step guide through the reloading process for IPSC, Steel Challenge and other action-shooting styles.
  • Safety Glasses 

You should always protect your eyes when reloading. Primers contain explosive compounds and nitrocellulose propellant is extremely flammable, with explosive characteristics when burning in a confined volume. We recommend:

  • Draeger X-pect safety glasses (Xpect) are made of tough, clear polycarbonate for indoor use, like reloading.
  • Rudy Project Rydon glasses (Rydon) are made of super-tough ImpactX material for superior protection, while reloading or when shooting. 
  • Vernier calliper 

Set and check cartridge dimensions, like crimp and overall length, we recommend:

  • CED digital calliper (CED-DigiCal). The calliper is not absolutely essential, but close enough that we included it here!
technical_specifications:
Ram diameter 1½” 
Loading rate
  • 800 to 1 000 rounds per hour
Height (from bench)
  • Without the optional electric case feeder: 32" (~800mm) 
  • With the electric case feeder installed: 38½" (~980mm) 
  • With optional XL650 mount: additional 175mm.
Capacity
  • Small Powder Bar - throws from a little under 3 to about 20 grains of powder.
  • Large Powder Bar - throws from 15 to nearly 45 grains of extruded type propellant, and from 20 to about 50 grains of ball/spherical type propellant.
NOTE: Capacities depend on actual propellant type, the values listed here are approximate.

Shooting Stuff has pre-configured this package for you for just one calibre, 9mm Luger. Your Dillon XL 650 can load many more calibres, and Calibre Conversion on the XL 650 is both as quick and easy as you want to make it. Dillon offers various levels of convenience to suit your requirements and budget. 

Option 1 - Minimum Kit 

As a minimum, you will need the following to change calibres:

  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
  • Reloading Die Set for the specific calibre.

Adding a Case Gauge for the specific calibre is always a good idea! 
Option 2 - Convenient Conversion

description:
The Dillon XL 650 Comprehensive Setup for 9mm Luger is a progressive reloader capable of loading 800 to 1 000 rounds of 9mm ammunition per hour. Shooting Stuff has included all the options and safety features, all the things that make the XL 650 South Africa's favourite. Barring the autodrive and bullet feeder, this is the "Full Monty"!

For complete peace of mind, the XL 650 is covered by Dillon’s legendary Lifetime "No-B.S." warranty. All electrical & electronic components in Dillon equipment are covered by a one-year warranty, as are textiles. Shooting Stuff fully supports Dillon’s warranty and has a spares cupboard with most spare parts available in stock. 

Click here to review a full description of the XL 650 and the many available options.

 Check each and every one of your cartridges for absolute confidence that none have high primers, none are cracked nor have other damage. If that sounds like too much effort just use the gauge occasionally to keep your reloading process in tune. Worth its weight in Stainless Steel!
  • Spare Parts Kit
 A collection of small parts that could easily get lost, or break, consider the Spare Parts Kit your insurance package until the Dillon Lifetime No-B.S. Warranty kicks in. After all, Murphy's Law states that if something can go wrong it will, and at the worst possible time (like the night before your match)
  • Setup

We will gladly setup your machine for you for FREE, as far as possible.

  • If you collect from us we can fully assemble the machine and included accessories, and then adjust the dies and powder charge.
  • If we ship the kit to you via courier, the extent of the setup is limited since we need to re-package the kit for safe shipping. We can install and adjust the dies, and set the powder charge, but you'll need to assemble all the bits.

Please add notes when checking out & finalising your purchase that include your load details, or send us an e-mail once your order is confirmed. If you want to assemble and setup everything yourself, learning the most about your machine, just omit the notes at check-out - simple!

categories: Shooting Stuff/Reloading/Reloading Machines/Configured Kits/SDB,Shooting Stuff/Reloading/Reloading Machines/Configured Kits,Shooting Stuff/Reloading/Reloading Machines,Shooting Stuff/Reloading
name: Dillon SDB Sensible Minimum Setup for 9mm Luger
description:
The Dillon SDB Sensible Minimum Setup for 9mm Luger is a compact progressive reloader capable of loading 300 to 400 rounds of 9mm ammunition per hour. Shooting Stuff has included the most essential options to enable you to start loading your 9mm ammo on the Dillon Square Deal B.

Not as robustly constructed as the larger RL 550 or XL 650, the SDB is intended for “occasional shooters” who load fewer than ~500 rounds per month, or 6 000 rounds per year. The Square Deal B only loads popular handgun calibres, no rifle calibres!

For complete peace of mind, the SDB is covered by Dillon’s legendary Lifetime "No-B.S." warranty. All electrical & electronic components in Dillon equipment are covered by a one-year warranty, as are textiles. Shooting Stuff fully supports Dillon’s warranty and has a spares cupboard with most spare parts available in stock. 

Click here to review a full description of the SDB and the many available options.
short_description: The Dillon SDB Sensible Minimum Setup for 9mm Luger is a compact progressive reloader capable of loading 300 to 400 rounds of 9mm ammunition per hour. Shooting Stuff has included the most essential options to enable you to start loading your 9mm ammo on the Dillon Square Deal B.
meta_title: Dillon SDB Sensible Minimum Setup for 9mm Luger | Reloading Presses | Shooting Stuff
meta_keywords: Dillon SDB Sensible Minimum Setup for 9mm Luger
meta_description: Looking for Dillon SDB Sensible Minimum Setup for 9mm Luger? Shooting Stuff has a large range of shooting products and accessories. Buy online today!
calibre_conversion:
Calibre Conversion on the SDB is both as quick and easy as you want to make it. Dillon offers various levels of convenience to suit your requirements and budget. While it does take a little longer to change calibres on the SDB than on the RL 550B or XL 650, it is straight-forward and quite quick. 

Option 1 - Minimum Kit 

 As a minimum, you will need the following to change calibres:

  • Appropriate calibre conversion kit, that includes the SDB-die set
  • Adding a Case Gauge for the specific calibre is always a good idea! 
Option 2 - Convenient Conversion

Option 1 does not take full advantage of the convenience offered by the SDB’s interchangeable tool head. So, if you want to leave your dies pre-set, you'll need:

  • Appropriate calibre conversion kit, that includes the SDB-die set
  • SDB Quick Change Kit (DLN-16378), we always believe that a Case Gauge for the specific calibre would be a good idea! 
Option 3 - The Easy Way 

For the full Dillon convenience of changing calibres, consider the option to leave your dies and powder system set up and dedicated to a specific cartridge for faster, easier calibre changes. We call this 'Calibre Conversion, the Easy Way':

  • Appropriate calibre conversion kit,which includes
    • Powder measure (DLN-20001)
    • SDB powder die (DLN-13865)
    • Tool head (DLN-20113)
  • SDB Tool head stand (DLN-62225)
  • Quick-change Dust Cover (DLN-11143) keeps the assembled tool head with powder measure dust free.
  • Case Gauge for the specific calibre (if available).
key_features:
• 4-station, progressive reloading machine:
    • Station 1: Resize and de-prime (at the top)
    • Station 2: Seat a new primer (at the bottom), then flare and dispense propellant (at the top)
    • Station 3: Seat the bullet (at the top)
    • Station 4: Crimps the cartridge case (at the top)
  • Insert cartridge cases and bullets manually.
  • Index the shell plate automatically.
  • Loads a limited list of handgun calibres only (requires additional calibre-specific items), including popular calibres like:
    • 9mm Luger, .38 Spl, .357 Mag, .38 Super, .40 S&W, .45 ACP, .44 Mag, etc.
  • Interchangeable tool head, for quick and easy calibre conversion.
  • Accepts proprietary SDB-dies only – one set included
  • Comes from the factory adjusted and ready to use!
optional_accesories: Click here for a comprehensive list of optional accessories.
package_contents:
Shooting Stuff's Sensible Minimum Setup for SDB system comprises the following:

  • SDB machine

This is "the big white box" that includes the main reloading machine and 

  • Proprietary SDB dies, already adjusted
  • Priming system
  • Primer early warning system
  • Operating handle, with knob
  • Powder measure, with the appropriate powder bar installed (usually small)
  • Ejected Catridge Chute Bracket
  • SDB Cartridge bin, (small, blue plastic AkroBin)
  • SDB Accessory Bag
  • Empty Calibre Conversion Kit Storage Box (Blue)
  • Printed Instruction Manual
  • SDB Spanner
  • Shooting Stuff's SDB-specific spanner gets in to the small space available on the tool head so that you can adjust the dies as required. Conventional spanners and shifters are just too bulky!
  • Primer Flip Tray
  • Dillon's metal flip tray is used to quickly get primers "the right way up" after dispensing these from their tray. 
  • Case lube
  • While not absolutely essential when using carbide dies, we highly recommend Dillon's easy-to-apply, spray-on case lube. Trust us on this - you'll feel the difference!
  • Case Gauge
  • Check each and every one of your 9mm cartridges for absolute confidence that none have high primers, none are cracked nor have other damage. If that sounds like too much effort just use the gauge occasionally to keep your reloading process in tune. Worth its weight in Stainless Steel!
  • Setup

We will gladly setup your machine for you for FREE, as far as possible.

  • If you collect from us we can fully assemble the machine and included accessories, and then adjust the dies and powder charge.
  • If we ship the kit to you via courier, the extent of the setup is limited since we need to re-package the kit for safe shipping. We can adjust the dies to your requiremnts, and set the powder charge, but you'll need to assemble all the bits.

Please make notes when checking out & finalising your purchase that include your load details, or send us an e-mail once your order is confirmed. If you want to assemble and setup everything yourself, learning the most about your machine, just omit the notes at check-out - simple!
recommended_accesories: Click here for a comprehensive list of recommended accessories.
required_accesories:
You will also need the following items (not included with this kit) to reload:

  • Scale

Set and periodically check your powder charge, we recommend one of the following: 

  • Dillon D-Terminator electronic scale (DLN-10483), and protective case (CED-SCase)
  • Dillon Eliminator balance-beam scale (DLN-13480)
  • CED Universal digital pocket scale (CED-UDPS)
  • Loading Manual
  • RDM’s Somchem reloading manual, version 2 (SomchemManual) is the only manual to include data for local, South African propellants.
  • DVD: Competition Reloading with Brian Enos (DLN-14341) - a step-by-step guide through the reloading process for IPSC, Steel Challenge and other action-shooting styles.
  • Safety Glasses 

You should always protect your eyes when reloading. Primers contain explosive compounds and nitrocellulose propellant is extremely flammable, with explosive characteristics when burning in a confined volume. We recommend:

  • Draeger X-pect safety glasses (Xpect) are made of tough, clear polycarbonate for indoor use, like reloading.
  • Rudy Project Rydon glasses (Rydon) are made of super-tough ImpactX material for superior protection, while reloading or when shooting. 
  • Vernier calliper 

Set and check cartridge dimensions, like crimp and overall length, we recommend:

  • CED digital calliper (CED-DigiCal). The calliper is not absolutely essential, but close enough that we included it here!
technical_specifications:
Loading rate
  • 400 to 500 rounds per hour
Height (from bench)
  • 18½" (~470mm)
  • with optional strong mount - additional 9” (~220mm) 
Capacity
  • Small Bar - throws from a little under 3 grains to about 20 grains of powder.
  • Large Bar - throws from around 15 grains to nearly 45 grains of extruded type propellant, and from around 20 to about 50 grains of ball/spherical type propellant. 

NOTE: Capacities depend on actual propellant type, the values listed here are approximate.

,package_contents=

Shooting Stuff's Sensible Minimum Setup for SDB system comprises the following:

  • SDB machine

This is "the big white box" that includes the main reloading machine and 

  • Proprietary SDB dies, already adjusted
  • Priming system
  • Primer early warning system
  • Operating handle, with knob
  • Powder measure, with the appropriate powder bar installed (usually small)
  • Ejected Catridge Chute Bracket
  • SDB Cartridge bin, (small, blue plastic AkroBin)
  • SDB Accessory Bag
  • Empty Calibre Conversion Kit Storage Box (Blue)
  • Printed Instruction Manual
  • SDB Spanner
  • Shooting Stuff's SDB-specific spanner gets in to the small space available on the tool head so that you can adjust the dies as required. Conventional spanners and shifters are just too bulky!
  • Primer Flip Tray
  • Dillon's metal flip tray is used to quickly get primers "the right way up" after dispensing these from their tray. 
  • Case lube
  • While not absolutely essential when using carbide dies, we highly recommend Dillon's easy-to-apply, spray-on case lube. Trust us on this - you'll feel the difference!
  • Case Gauge
  • Check each and every one of your 9mm cartridges for absolute confidence that none have high primers, none are cracked nor have other damage. If that sounds like too much effort just use the gauge occasionally to keep your reloading process in tune. Worth its weight in Stainless Steel!
  • Setup

We will gladly setup your machine for you for FREE, as far as possible.

  • If you collect from us we can fully assemble the machine and included accessories, and then adjust the dies and powder charge.
  • If we ship the kit to you via courier, the extent of the setup is limited since we need to re-package the kit for safe shipping. We can adjust the dies to your requiremnts, and set the powder charge, but you'll need to assemble all the bits.

Please make notes when checking out & finalising your purchase that include your load details, or send us an e-mail once your order is confirmed. If you want to assemble and setup everything yourself, learning the most about your machine, just omit the notes at check-out - simple!

,required_accesories=

You will also need the following items (not included with this kit) to reload:

  • Scale

Set and periodically check your powder charge, we recommend one of the following: 

  • Dillon D-Terminator electronic scale (DLN-10483), and protective case (CED-SCase)
  • Dillon Eliminator balance-beam scale (DLN-13480)
  • CED Universal digital pocket scale (CED-UDPS)
  • Loading Manual
  • RDM’s Somchem reloading manual, version 2 (SomchemManual) is the only manual to include data for local, South African propellants.
  • DVD: Competition Reloading with Brian Enos (DLN-14341) - a step-by-step guide through the reloading process for IPSC, Steel Challenge and other action-shooting styles.
  • Safety Glasses 

You should always protect your eyes when reloading. Primers contain explosive compounds and nitrocellulose propellant is extremely flammable, with explosive characteristics when burning in a confined volume. We recommend:

  • Draeger X-pect safety glasses (Xpect) are made of tough, clear polycarbonate for indoor use, like reloading.
  • Rudy Project Rydon glasses (Rydon) are made of super-tough ImpactX material for superior protection, while reloading or when shooting. 
  • Vernier calliper 

Set and check cartridge dimensions, like crimp and overall length, we recommend:

  • CED digital calliper (CED-DigiCal). The calliper is not absolutely essential, but close enough that we included it here!

key_features:
• 4-station, progressive reloading machine:
    • Station 1: Resize and de-prime (at the top)

  • Comes from the factory adjusted and ready to use!

Not as robustly constructed as the larger RL 550 or XL 650, the SDB is intended for “occasional shooters” who load fewer than ~500 rounds per month, or 6 000 rounds per year. The Square Deal B only loads popular handgun calibres, no rifle calibres!

calibre_conversion:
Calibre Conversion on the SDB is both as quick and easy as you want to make it. Dillon offers various levels of convenience to suit your requirements and budget. While it does take a little longer to change calibres on the SDB than on the RL 550B or XL 650, it is straight-forward and quite quick. 

Option 1 - Minimum Kit 

 As a minimum, you will need the following to change calibres:

  • Appropriate calibre conversion kit, that includes the SDB-die set
  • Adding a Case Gauge for the specific calibre is always a good idea! 
Option 2 - Convenient Conversion

Option 1 does not take full advantage of the convenience offered by the SDB’s interchangeable tool head. So, if you want to leave your dies pre-set, you'll need:

  • Appropriate calibre conversion kit, that includes the SDB-die set
  • SDB Quick Change Kit (DLN-16378), we always believe that a Case Gauge for the specific calibre would be a good idea! 
Option 3 - The Easy Way 

For the full Dillon convenience of changing calibres, consider the option to leave your dies and powder system set up and dedicated to a specific cartridge for faster, easier calibre changes. We call this 'Calibre Conversion, the Easy Way':

  • Appropriate calibre conversion kit,which includes
    • Powder measure (DLN-20001)
    • SDB powder die (DLN-13865)
    • Tool head (DLN-20113)
  • SDB Tool head stand (DLN-62225)
  • Quick-change Dust Cover (DLN-11143) keeps the assembled tool head with powder measure dust free.
  • Case Gauge for the specific calibre (if available).

package_contents:
Shooting Stuff's Recommended Setup for SDB system comprises the following:

  • SDB machine

This is "the big white box" that includes the main reloading machine and 

  • Proprietary SDB dies, already adjusted
  • Priming system
  • Primer early warning system
  • Operating handle, with knob

  • Machine Mount
  • Shooting Stuff's blue, powder coated machine mount raises the entire SDB above the bench's top, and spreads the load. A more stable system simply loads better! If necessary, the assembled SDB-system stands securely on the machine mount.
  • Cartridge Case Bin & Bracket
  • Shooting Stuff's Cartridge Case Bin & Bracket (SDB) is a kit that positions the empty cardridge cases conveniently on the right-hand side of the Dillon Square Deal B progressive reloading machine, ready for inserting into station 1. 
  • Bullet Tray
  • Dillon's cast Bullet Tray mounts to the left plate of the machine mount, and holds a few hundred bullets conveniently close to where they're needed.
  • Toolkit
  • Shooting Stuff's Toolkit for the SDB is a stylish, one-piece bracket that mounts to the "blue" Dillon progressive reloading machines to organise and store a set of ball-ended Allen wrenches and the 1-inch spanner. These tools are supplied in the kit and are what's required to adjust and basically service the machine.
  • Primer Flip Tray
  • Dillon's metal flip tray is used to quickly get primers "the right way up" after dispensing these from their tray. 
  • Primer Pick-up Tubes
  • A pack of 4 additional primer pick-up tubes used to pick-up small primers from the Flip Tray. Together with the one included with the reloading machine you'll be able to pre-fill 500 primers so that you can conveniently load a substantail batch of ammo with minimum interuption to replenish components.
  • Case lube
  • While not absolutely essential when using carbide dies, we highly recommend Dillon's easy-to-apply, spray-on case lube. Trust us on this - you'll feel the difference!

  • Check each and every one of your 9mm cartridges for absolute confidence that none have high primers, none are cracked nor have other damage. If that sounds like too much effort just use the gauge occasionally to keep your reloading process in tune. Worth its weight in Stainless Steel!
  • DVD Instruction Manual
  • Video conveys so much more than printed pictures and text. You won't find this info on YouTube!
  • Spare Parts Kit
  • A collection of small parts that could easily get lost, or break, consider the Spare Parts Kit your insurance package until the Dillon Lifetime No-B.S. Warranty kicks in. After all, Murphy's Law states that if something can go wrong it will, and at the worst possible time (like the night before your match)
  • Setup

  • If you collect from us we can fully assemble the machine and included accessories, and then adjust the dies and powder charge.

key_features:
• 4-station, progressive reloading machine:
    • Station 1: Resize and de-prime (at the top)
    • Station 2: Seat a new primer (at the bottom), then flare and dispense propellant (at the top)
    • Station 3: Seat the bullet (at the top)
    • Station 4: Crimps the cartridge case (at the top)
  • Insert cartridge cases and bullets manually.
  • Index the shell plate automatically.
  • Loads a limited list of handgun calibres only (requires additional calibre-specific items), including popular calibres like:
    • 9mm Luger, .38 Spl, .357 Mag, .38 Super, .40 S&W, .45 ACP, .44 Mag, etc.
  • Interchangeable tool head, for quick and easy calibre conversion.
  • Accepts proprietary SDB-dies only – one set included
  • Comes from the factory adjusted and ready to use!
package_contents:
Shooting Stuff's Recommended Setup for SDB system comprises the following:

  • SDB machine

This is "the big white box" that includes the main reloading machine and 

  • Proprietary SDB dies, already adjusted
  • Priming system
  • Primer early warning system
  • Operating handle, with knob
  • Powder measure, with the appropriate powder bar installed (usually small)
  • Ejected Catridge Chute Bracket
  • SDB Cartridge bin, (small, blue plastic AkroBin)
  • SDB Accessory Bag
  • Empty Calibre Conversion Kit Storage Box (Blue)
  • Printed Instruction Manual
  • Machine Mount
  • Shooting Stuff's blue, powder coated machine mount raises the entire SDB above the bench's top, and spreads the load. A more stable system simply loads better! If necessary, the assembled SDB-system stands securely on the machine mount.
  • Cartridge Case Bin & Bracket
  • Shooting Stuff's Cartridge Case Bin & Bracket (SDB) is a kit that positions the empty cardridge cases conveniently on the right-hand side of the Dillon Square Deal B progressive reloading machine, ready for inserting into station 1. 
  • Bullet Tray
  • Dillon's cast Bullet Tray mounts to the left plate of the machine mount, and holds a few hundred bullets conveniently close to where they're needed.
  • Toolkit
  • Shooting Stuff's Toolkit for the SDB is a stylish, one-piece bracket that mounts to the "blue" Dillon progressive reloading machines to organise and store a set of ball-ended Allen wrenches and the 1-inch spanner. These tools are supplied in the kit and are what's required to adjust and basically service the machine.
  • Primer Flip Tray
  • Dillon's metal flip tray is used to quickly get primers "the right way up" after dispensing these from their tray. 
  • Primer Pick-up Tubes
  • A pack of 4 additional primer pick-up tubes used to pick-up small primers from the Flip Tray. Together with the one included with the reloading machine you'll be able to pre-fill 500 primers so that you can conveniently load a substantail batch of ammo with minimum interuption to replenish components.
  • Case lube
  • While not absolutely essential when using carbide dies, we highly recommend Dillon's easy-to-apply, spray-on case lube. Trust us on this - you'll feel the difference!
  • Case Gauge
  • Check each and every one of your 9mm cartridges for absolute confidence that none have high primers, none are cracked nor have other damage. If that sounds like too much effort just use the gauge occasionally to keep your reloading process in tune. Worth its weight in Stainless Steel!
  • DVD Instruction Manual
  • Video conveys so much more than printed pictures and text. You won't find this info on YouTube!
  • Spare Parts Kit
  • A collection of small parts that could easily get lost, or break, consider the Spare Parts Kit your insurance package until the Dillon Lifetime No-B.S. Warranty kicks in. After all, Murphy's Law states that if something can go wrong it will, and at the worst possible time (like the night before your match)
  • Setup

We will gladly setup your machine for you for FREE, as far as possible.

  • If you collect from us we can fully assemble the machine and included accessories, and then adjust the dies and powder charge.
  • If we ship the kit to you via courier, the extent of the setup is limited since we need to re-package the kit for safe shipping. We can install and adjust the dies, and set the powder charge, but you'll need to assemble all the bits.

Please make notes when checking out & finalising your purchase that include your load details, or send us an e-mail once your order is confirmed. If you want to assemble and setup everything yourself, learning the most about your machine, just omit the notes at check-out - simple!

name: Dillon SDB Comprehensive Setup for 9mm Luger
description:
The Dillon SDB Comprehensive Setup for 9mm Luger is a compact progressive reloader capable of loading 300 to 400 rounds of 9mm ammunition per hour. This is the "Full Monty" - Shooting Stuff has included the all options to enable you to comfortably load your 9mm ammo on the Dillon Square Deal B.

Not as robustly constructed as the larger RL 550 or XL 650, the SDB is intended for “occasional shooters” who load fewer than ~500 rounds per month, or 6 000 rounds per year. The Square Deal B only loads popular handgun calibres, no rifle calibres!

For complete peace of mind, the SDB is covered by Dillon’s legendary Lifetime "No-B.S." warranty. All electrical & electronic components in Dillon equipment are covered by a one-year warranty, as are textiles. Shooting Stuff fully supports Dillon’s warranty and has a spares cupboard with most spare parts available in stock. 

Click here to review a full description of the SDB and the many available options.

calibre_conversion:
Calibre Conversion on the SDB is both as quick and easy as you want to make it. Dillon offers various levels of convenience to suit your requirements and budget. While it does take a little longer to change calibres on the SDB than on the RL 550B or XL 650, it is straight-forward and quite quick. 

Option 1 - Minimum Kit 

 As a minimum, you will need the following to change calibres:

  • Appropriate calibre conversion kit, that includes the SDB-die set
  • Adding a Case Gauge for the specific calibre is always a good idea! 
Option 2 - Convenient Conversion

Option 1 does not take full advantage of the convenience offered by the SDB’s interchangeable tool head. So, if you want to leave your dies pre-set, you'll need:

  • Appropriate calibre conversion kit, that includes the SDB-die set
  • SDB Quick Change Kit (DLN-16378), we always believe that a Case Gauge for the specific calibre would be a good idea! 
Option 3 - The Easy Way 

For the full Dillon convenience of changing calibres, consider the option to leave your dies and powder system set up and dedicated to a specific cartridge for faster, easier calibre changes. We call this 'Calibre Conversion, the Easy Way':

  • Appropriate calibre conversion kit,which includes
    • Powder measure (DLN-20001)
    • SDB powder die (DLN-13865)
    • Tool head (DLN-20113)
  • SDB Tool head stand (DLN-62225)
  • Quick-change Dust Cover (DLN-11143) keeps the assembled tool head with powder measure dust free.
  • Case Gauge for the specific calibre (if available).

    • Station 2: Seat a new primer (at the bottom), then flare and dispense propellant (at the top)

    • Station 4: Crimps the cartridge case (at the top)
  • Insert cartridge cases and bullets manually.
  • Index the shell plate automatically.
  • Loads a limited list of handgun calibres only (requires additional calibre-specific items), including popular calibres like:
    • 9mm Luger, .38 Spl, .357 Mag, .38 Super, .40 S&W, .45 ACP, .44 Mag, etc.
  • Interchangeable tool head, for quick and easy calibre conversion.
  • Accepts proprietary SDB-dies only – one set included
  • Comes from the factory adjusted and ready to use!

  • Priming system

  • Machine Mount
  • Shooting Stuff's blue, powder coated machine mount raises the entire SDB above the bench's top, and spreads the load. A more stable system simply loads better! If necessary, the assembled SDB-system stands securely on the machine mount.
  • Cartridge Case Bin & Bracket
  • Shooting Stuff's Cartridge Case Bin & Bracket (SDB) is a kit that positions the empty cardridge cases conveniently on the right-hand side of the Dillon Square Deal B progressive reloading machine, ready for inserting into station 1. 
  • Bullet Tray
  • Dillon's cast Bullet Tray mounts to the left plate of the machine mount, and holds a few hundred bullets conveniently close to where they're needed.
  • Toolkit
  • Shooting Stuff's Toolkit for the SDB is a stylish, one-piece bracket that mounts to the "blue" Dillon progressive reloading machines to organise and store a set of ball-ended Allen wrenches and the 1-inch spanner. These tools are supplied in the kit and are what's required to adjust and basically service the machine.
  • Smooth-glide Roller Handle
  • Shooting Stuff's roller handle runs on sealed bearings for enhanced reloading comfort and tactile feedback when seating primers. We developed this one specifically for the SDB.
  • Low Powder Sensor
  • This is a warning system that provides an audible and visual reminder when it's time to refill your powder reservoir.
  • SDB Machine Cover
  • Shooting Stuff's SDB Machine Cover is perfect for keeping your equipment clean and free of dust, when not in use.This cover is suitable for the Dillon RL550 and SDB progressive reloading machines.
  • Primer Flip Tray
  • Dillon's metal flip tray is used to quickly get primers "the right way up" after dispensing these from their tray. 
  • Primer Pick-up Tubes
  • A pack of 4 additional primer pick-up tubes used to pick-up small primers from the Flip Tray. Together with the one included with the reloading machine you'll be able to pre-fill 500 primers so that you can conveniently load a substantail batch of ammo with minimum interuption to replenish components.
  • Case lube
  • While not absolutely essential when using carbide dies, we highly recommend Dillon's easy-to-apply, spray-on case lube. Trust us on this - you'll feel the difference!
  • Case Gauge
  • Check each and every one of your 9mm cartridges for absolute confidence that none have high primers, none are cracked nor have other damage. If that sounds like too much effort just use the gauge occasionally to keep your reloading process in tune. Worth its weight in Stainless Steel!
  • DVD Instruction Manual
  • Video conveys so much more than printed pictures and text. You won't find this info on YouTube!
  • Spare Parts Kit
  • A collection of small parts that could easily get lost, or break, consider the Spare Parts Kit your insurance package until the Dillon Lifetime No-B.S. Warranty kicks in. After all, Murphy's Law states that if something can go wrong it will, and at the worst possible time (like the night before your match)

  • If you collect from us we can fully assemble the machine and included accessories, and then adjust the dies and powder charge.
  • If we ship the kit to you via courier, the extent of the setup is limited since we need to re-package the kit for safe shipping. We can install and adjust the dies, and set the powder charge, but you'll need to assemble all the bits.

Please make notes when checking out & finalising your purchase that include your load details, or send us an e-mail once your order is confirmed. If you want to assemble and setup everything yourself, learning the most about your machine, just omit the notes at check-out - simple!
recommended_accesories: Click here for a comprehensive list of recommended accessories
required_accesories:
You will also need the following items (not included with this kit) to reload:

  • Scale

Set and periodically check your powder charge, we recommend one of the following: 

  • Dillon D-Terminator electronic scale (DLN-10483), and protective case (CED-SCase)
  • Dillon Eliminator balance-beam scale (DLN-13480)
  • CED Universal digital pocket scale (CED-UDPS)
  • Loading Manual
  • RDM’s Somchem reloading manual, version 2 (SomchemManual) is the only manual to include data for local, South African propellants.
  • DVD: Competition Reloading with Brian Enos (DLN-14341) - a step-by-step guide through the reloading process for IPSC, Steel Challenge and other action-shooting styles.
  • Safety Glasses 

You should always protect your eyes when reloading. Primers contain explosive compounds and nitrocellulose propellant is extremely flammable, with explosive characteristics when burning in a confined volume. We recommend:

  • Draeger X-pect safety glasses (Xpect) are made of tough, clear polycarbonate for indoor use, like reloading.
  • Rudy Project Rydon glasses (Rydon) are made of super-tough ImpactX material for superior protection, while reloading or when shooting. 
  • Vernier calliper 

Set and check cartridge dimensions, like crimp and overall length, we recommend:

  • CED digital calliper (CED-DigiCal). The calliper is not absolutely essential, but close enough that we included it here!
technical_specifications:
Loading rate
  • 400 to 500 rounds per hour
Height (from bench)
  • 18½" (~470mm)
  • with optional strong mount - additional 9” (~220mm) 
Capacity
  • Small Bar - throws from a little under 3 grains to about 20 grains of powder.
  • Large Bar - throws from around 15 grains to nearly 45 grains of extruded type propellant, and from around 20 to about 50 grains of ball/spherical type propellant. 

NOTE: Capacities depend on actual propellant type, the values listed here are approximate.

    • 9mm Luger, .38 Spl, .357 Mag, .38 Super, .40 S&W, .45 ACP, .44 Mag, etc.
  • Interchangeable tool head, for quick and easy calibre conversion.
  • Accepts proprietary SDB-dies only – one set included
  • Comes from the factory adjusted and ready to use!
package_contents:
Shooting Stuff's Comprehensive Setup for SDB system comprises the following:

  • SDB machine

This is "the big white box" that includes the main reloading machine and 

  • Proprietary SDB dies, already adjusted
  • Priming system
  • Primer early warning system
  • Operating handle, with knob
  • Powder measure, with the appropriate powder bar installed (usually small)
  • Ejected Catridge Chute Bracket
  • SDB Cartridge bin, (small, blue plastic AkroBin)
  • SDB Accessory Bag
  • Empty Calibre Conversion Kit Storage Box (Blue)
  • Printed Instruction Manual
  • Machine Mount
  • Shooting Stuff's blue, powder coated machine mount raises the entire SDB above the bench's top, and spreads the load. A more stable system simply loads better! If necessary, the assembled SDB-system stands securely on the machine mount.
  • Cartridge Case Bin & Bracket
  • Shooting Stuff's Cartridge Case Bin & Bracket (SDB) is a kit that positions the empty cardridge cases conveniently on the right-hand side of the Dillon Square Deal B progressive reloading machine, ready for inserting into station 1. 
  • Bullet Tray
  • Dillon's cast Bullet Tray mounts to the left plate of the machine mount, and holds a few hundred bullets conveniently close to where they're needed.
  • Toolkit
  • Shooting Stuff's Toolkit for the SDB is a stylish, one-piece bracket that mounts to the "blue" Dillon progressive reloading machines to organise and store a set of ball-ended Allen wrenches and the 1-inch spanner. These tools are supplied in the kit and are what's required to adjust and basically service the machine.
  • Smooth-glide Roller Handle
  • Shooting Stuff's roller handle runs on sealed bearings for enhanced reloading comfort and tactile feedback when seating primers. We developed this one specifically for the SDB.
  • Low Powder Sensor
  • This is a warning system that provides an audible and visual reminder when it's time to refill your powder reservoir.
  • SDB Machine Cover
  • Shooting Stuff's SDB Machine Cover is perfect for keeping your equipment clean and free of dust, when not in use.This cover is suitable for the Dillon RL550 and SDB progressive reloading machines.
  • Primer Flip Tray
  • Dillon's metal flip tray is used to quickly get primers "the right way up" after dispensing these from their tray. 
  • Primer Pick-up Tubes
  • A pack of 4 additional primer pick-up tubes used to pick-up small primers from the Flip Tray. Together with the one included with the reloading machine you'll be able to pre-fill 500 primers so that you can conveniently load a substantail batch of ammo with minimum interuption to replenish components.
  • Case lube
  • While not absolutely essential when using carbide dies, we highly recommend Dillon's easy-to-apply, spray-on case lube. Trust us on this - you'll feel the difference!
  • Case Gauge
  • Check each and every one of your 9mm cartridges for absolute confidence that none have high primers, none are cracked nor have other damage. If that sounds like too much effort just use the gauge occasionally to keep your reloading process in tune. Worth its weight in Stainless Steel!
  • DVD Instruction Manual
  • Video conveys so much more than printed pictures and text. You won't find this info on YouTube!
  • Spare Parts Kit
  • A collection of small parts that could easily get lost, or break, consider the Spare Parts Kit your insurance package until the Dillon Lifetime No-B.S. Warranty kicks in. After all, Murphy's Law states that if something can go wrong it will, and at the worst possible time (like the night before your match)
  • Setup

We will gladly setup your machine for you for FREE, as far as possible.

  • If you collect from us we can fully assemble the machine and included accessories, and then adjust the dies and powder charge.
  • If we ship the kit to you via courier, the extent of the setup is limited since we need to re-package the kit for safe shipping. We can install and adjust the dies, and set the powder charge, but you'll need to assemble all the bits.

Please make notes when checking out & finalising your purchase that include your load details, or send us an e-mail once your order is confirmed. If you want to assemble and setup everything yourself, learning the most about your machine, just omit the notes at check-out - simple!

name: Dillon RL 550 Comprehensive Setup for 9mm Luger
description:
The Dillon RL 550 Comprehensive Setup for 9mm Luger is a progressive reloader capable of loading 400 to 500 rounds of 9mm ammunition per hour. Shooting Stuff has included all the options and safety features, all the things that make the RL 550 Dillon’s most popular reloader worldwide. Barring the bullet feeder, this is the "Full Monty"!

For complete peace of mind, the RL 550 is covered by Dillon’s legendary Lifetime "No-B.S." warranty. All electrical & electronic components in Dillon equipment are covered by a one-year warranty, as are textiles. Shooting Stuff fully supports Dillon’s warranty and has a spares cupboard with most spare parts available in stock.

Click here to review a full description of the RL 550 and the many available options.

calibre_conversion:
Calibre Conversion on the RL 550C is both as quick and easy as you want to make it. Dillon offers various levels of convenience to suit your requirements and budget.

Option 1 - Minimum Kit   As a minimum, you will need the following to change calibres:
  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
  • Reloading Die Set for the specific calibre.

Adding a Case Gauge for the specific calibre is always a good idea! 
Option 2 - Convenient Conversion

Option 1 does not take full advantage of the convenience offered by the RL 550C’s interchangeable tool head. So, if you want to leave your dies pre-set, you'll need:

  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
  • Reloading Die Set for the specific calibre.
  • Dillon RL 550C Tool Head (DLN-13909)

Including an additional powder die allows you to move your powder measure from tool head to tool head without changing the flare or belling adjustment. Choose from:

  • Dillon Powder Die (DLN-20064)
  • Dillon Oversize Powder Die (DLN-21253) for calibres too large in diameter to fit into the standard powder die.

We call this 'Convenient Calibre Conversion', a.k.a. the moderately easy way. If you don't already have one, we always believe that a Case Gauge for the specific calibre would be a good idea! 
Option 3 - The Easy Way 

For the full Dillon convenience of changing calibres, consider the option to leave your dies and powder system set up and dedicated to a specific cartridge for faster, easier calibre changes. We call this 'Calibre Conversion, the Easy Way':

  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
  • Reloading Die Set for the specific calibre.
  • Dillon RL 550C Quick Change Kit (DLN-22058), which includes:
    • Dillon Powder Measure (DLN-20782)
    • Dillon Powder Die (DLN-20064)
    • Dillon RL 550C Tool Head (DLN-13909)
    • Dillon Toolhead Stand (DLN-22055)
  • Quick-change Dust Cover (DLN-11143) keeps the assembled tool head with powder measure dust free.
  • Case Gauge for the specific calibre (if available).

If you already have the optional electric case feeder you may need a different case feed plate. Please refer to the calibre conversion chart in the Instruction Manual for the correct plate. The RL 550 C Instruction Manual can be downloaded here, or call Shooting Stuff for advice. Available case feed plates (applicable to the RL 550 C) are:

  • Dillon Large Pistol Case Feed Plate (DLN-21072)
  • Dillon Small Pistol Case Feed Plate (DLN-21073)
key_features:
•  4-station, progressive reloading machine:
    • Station 1. Resize and deprime, seat a new primer
    • Station 2. Flare handgun cases, dispense propellant
    • Station 3. Seat the bullet
    • Station 4. Crimp the cartridge case
  • Insert cartridge cases manually.
  • Index the shell plate manually.
  • Feed and insert new primers automatically.
  • Dispense propellant automatically.
  • Operator places bullets manually.
  • Eject loaded cartridges automatically.
  • Loads most popular rifle and handgun calibres (requires additional calibre-specific items).
  • Accepts standard ⅞” x 14 tpi (thread per inch) dies. - Dillon dies are designed for high speed use, as well as rapid cleaning. Non-Dillon dies must re-size and de-prime in the same die. Note that the case flaring die from other brands is not used on the RL 550B, as this function is covered from the calibre conversion kit and powder die.
  • Interchangeable tool head, for quick and easy calibre conversion.

recommended_accesories:
Primer Transfer 

Dillon offers a manual system of flip tray and pick-up tubes or an automated system to get the primers from their shipping box into the RL 550 primer magazine. While the manual approach is most popular - that's why they're included with this kit - the RF 100 is really convenient! Consider this a reminder ...

  • RF 100 Automatic Primer Filler 
 The Dillon RF 100 Automatic Primer Filler is an electrically powered machine to sort and transfer a hundred primers from their packaging box into a "transfer tube", for subsequent transfer into the primer magazine of your favourite Dillon progressive reloading machine. The RF 100 eliminates the need to manually fill primer pick-up tubes, and is available for either large or small primers with conversion kits to change to the other size.
  • RF 100 for large primers, 220V (DLN-97112)
  • Conversion kit to load small primers (DLN-17903)
  • RF 100 for small primers, 220V (DLN-97113)
  • Conversion kit to load large primers (DLN-17902)
required_accesories:
You will also need the following (not included with the machine) to reload:

  • Scale 

Set and periodically check your powder charge, we recommend one of the following: 

  • Dillon D-Terminator electronic scale (DLN-10483), and protective case (CED-SCase)
  • Dillon Eliminator balance-beam scale (DLN-13480)
  • CED Universal digital pocket scale (CED-UDPS)
  • Loading Manual
  • RDM’s Somchem reloading manual, version 2 (SomchemManual) is the only manual to include data for local, South African propellants.
  • DVD: Competition Reloading with Brian Enos (DLN-14341) - a step-by-step guide through the reloading process for IPSC, Steel Challenge and other action-shooting styles.
  • Safety Glasses 

You should always protect your eyes when reloading. Primers contain explosive compounds and nitrocellulose propellant is extremely flammable, with explosive characteristics when burning in a confined volume. We recommend:

  • Draeger X-pect safety glasses (Xpect) are made of tough, clear polycarbonate for indoor use, like reloading.
  • Rudy Project Rydon glasses (Rydon) are made of super-tough ImpactX material for superior protection, while reloading or when shooting. 
  • Vernier calliper 

Set and check cartridge dimensions, like crimp and overall length, we recommend:

  • CED digital calliper (CED-DigiCal). The calliper is not absolutely essential, but close enough that we included it here!
technical_specifications:
Ram diameter 1½” 
Loading rate
  • 400 to 600 rounds per hour,
  • 800 rounds per hour when using the optional 220V electric case feeder
Height (from bench)
  • without optional electric case feeder - 21" (~535mm) 
  • with electric case feeder installed - 38½" (~980mm) 
  • with optional strong mount - additional 9” (~220mm) 
Capacity
  • Small Powder Bar - throws from a little under 3 to about 20 grains of powder.
  • Large Powder Bar - throws from 15 to nearly 45 grains of extruded type propellant, and from 20 to about 50 grains of ball/spherical type propellant.

Additional Powder bars (not included with the machine):

  • Dillon Extra Small Powder Bar (DLN-20780) - throws from ½ to about 3 grains.
  • Dillon Magnum Rifle Powder Bar (DLN-21353) - throws up to ~73 grains of extruded type propellant and ~82 grains of ball/spherical type propellant. 

 

NOTE: Capacities depend on actual propellant type, the values listed here are approximate.

While the manual approach is most popular - that's why they're included with this kit - the RF 100 is really convenient! Consider this a reminder ...

  • RF 100 Automatic Primer Filler 
 The Dillon RF 100 Automatic Primer Filler is an electrically powered machine to sort and transfer a hundred primers from their packaging box into a "transfer tube", for subsequent transfer into the primer magazine of your favourite Dillon progressive reloading machine. The RF 100 eliminates the need to manually fill primer pick-up tubes, and is available for either large or small primers with conversion kits to change to the other size.
  • RF 100 for large primers, 220V (DLN-97112)
  • Conversion kit to load small primers (DLN-17903)
  • RF 100 for small primers, 220V (DLN-97113)
  • Conversion kit to load large primers (DLN-17902)
,required_accesories=

You will also need the following (not included with the machine) to reload:

  • Scale 

Set and periodically check your powder charge, we recommend one of the following: 

  • Dillon D-Terminator electronic scale (DLN-10483), and protective case (CED-SCase)
  • Dillon Eliminator balance-beam scale (DLN-13480)
  • CED Universal digital pocket scale (CED-UDPS)
  • Loading Manual
  • RDM’s Somchem reloading manual, version 2 (SomchemManual) is the only manual to include data for local, South African propellants.
  • DVD: Competition Reloading with Brian Enos (DLN-14341) - a step-by-step guide through the reloading process for IPSC, Steel Challenge and other action-shooting styles.
  • Safety Glasses 

You should always protect your eyes when reloading. Primers contain explosive compounds and nitrocellulose propellant is extremely flammable, with explosive characteristics when burning in a confined volume. We recommend:

  • Draeger X-pect safety glasses (Xpect) are made of tough, clear polycarbonate for indoor use, like reloading.
  • Rudy Project Rydon glasses (Rydon) are made of super-tough ImpactX material for superior protection, while reloading or when shooting. 
  • Vernier calliper 

Set and check cartridge dimensions, like crimp and overall length, we recommend:

  • CED digital calliper (CED-DigiCal). The calliper is not absolutely essential, but close enough that we included it here!
,sw_featured=No,technical_specifications=
Ram diameter 1½” 
Loading rate
  • 400 to 600 rounds per hour,
  • 800 rounds per hour when using the optional 220V electric case feeder
Height (from bench)
  • without optional electric case feeder - 21" (~535mm) 
  • with electric case feeder installed - 38½" (~980mm) 
  • with optional strong mount - additional 9” (~220mm) 
Capacity
  • Small Powder Bar - throws from a little under 3 to about 20 grains of powder.
  • Large Powder Bar - throws from 15 to nearly 45 grains of extruded type propellant, and from 20 to about 50 grains of ball/spherical type propellant.

Additional Powder bars (not included with the machine):

  • Dillon Extra Small Powder Bar (DLN-20780) - throws from ½ to about 3 grains.
  • Dillon Magnum Rifle Powder Bar (DLN-21353) - throws up to ~73 grains of extruded type propellant and ~82 grains of ball/spherical type propellant. 

 

NOTE: Capacities depend on actual propellant type, the values listed here are approximate.

description:

Shooting Stuff has included all the options and safety features, all the things that make the RL 550 Dillon’s most popular reloader worldwide. Barring the bullet feeder, this is the "Full Monty"!

For complete peace of mind, the RL 550 is covered by Dillon’s legendary Lifetime "No-B.S." warranty. All electrical & electronic components in Dillon equipment are covered by a one-year warranty, as are textiles. Shooting Stuff fully supports Dillon’s warranty and has a spares cupboard with most spare parts available in stock.

Click here to review a full description of the RL 550 and the many available options.
package_contents:
Shooting Stuff's Comprehensive RL 550 system comprises the following:

  • RL 550B machine
 This is "the big white box" that includes the main reloading machine with the tool head and primer system already fitted and 
  • Calibre Conversion Kit Box, with calibre-specific parts for 9mm Luger
  • Primer early warning system
  • Operating handle, with knob
  • Powder measure
  • RL 550 Accessory Bag
  • RL 550 Accessory Box
  • Printed Instruction Manual
  • Dillon 9mm Carbide Die Set

3-die set for progressive relaoding machines:

  • Carbide sizing die with decapping assembly
  • Bullet seating die
  • Separate taper crimp die
  • Low Powder Sensor
 This is a warning system that provides an audible and visual reminder when it's time to refill your powder reservoir.
  • Machine Mount
 Shooting Stuff's blue, powder coated machine mount raises the entire RL 550 above the bench's top, and spreads the load. A more stable system simply loads better! If necessary, the assembled 550-system stands securely on the machine mount.
  • Bullet Tray
 Dillon's cast Bullet Tray mounts to the left plate of the machine mount, and holds a few hundred bullets conveniently close to where they're needed.
  • Cartridge Case Bin & Bracket
 The Shooting Stuff Cartridge Case Bin & Bracket (RL550) is a kit that positions the empty cardridge cases conveniently on the right-hand side of the Dillon RL550B progressive reloading machine, ready for inserting into station 1.
  • Toolkit
 Shooting Stuff's Toolkit for the RL 550 is a stylish, one-piece bracket that mounts to the "blue" Dillon progressive reloading machines to organise and store a set of ball-ended Allen wrenches and the 1-inch spanner. These tools are supplied in the kit and are what's required to adjust and basically service the machine.
  • Smooth-glide Roller Handle
 Shooting Stuff's roller handle runs on sealed bearings for enhanced reloading comfort and tactile feedback when seating primers.
  • Primer Flip Tray
 Dillon's metal flip tray is used to quickly get primers "the right way up" after dispensing these from their tray.
  • Primer Pick-up Tubes
 A pack of 4 additional primer pick-up tubes used to pick-up small primers from the Flip Tray. Together with the one included with the reloading machine you'll be able to pre-fill 500 primers so that you can conveniently load a substantail batch of ammo with minimum interuption to replenish components.
  • Case lube
 While not absolutely essential when using carbide dies, we highly recommend Dillon's easy-to-apply, spray-on case lube. Trust us on this - you'll feel the difference!
  • Case Gauge
 Check each and every one of your 9mm cartridges for absolute confidence that none have high primers, none are cracked nor have other damage. If that sounds like too much effort just use the gauge occasionally to keep your reloading process in tune. Worth its weight in Stainless Steel!
  • Spare Parts Kit
 A collection of small parts that could easily get lost, or break, consider the Spare Parts Kit your insurance package until the Dillon Lifetime No-B.S. Warranty kicks in. After all, Murphy's Law states that if something can go wrong it will, and at the worst possible time (like the night before your match)
  • Machine Cover
 Our machine covers are designed to keep the machine dust free. They have a locking feature to secure the machine from little hands, or other unauthorised tampering.
  • DVD Instruction Manual
 Video conveys so much more than printed pictures and text. You won't find this info on YouTube!
  • Setup

We will gladly setup your machine for you for FREE, as far as possible.

  • If you collect from us we can fully assemble the machine and included accessories, and then adjust the dies and powder charge.
  • If we ship the kit to you via courier, the extent of the setup is limited since we need to re-package the kit for safe shipping. We can install and adjust the dies, and set the powder charge, but you'll need to assemble all the bits.

 

Please make notes when checking out & finalising your purchase that include your load details, or send us an e-mail once your order is confirmed. If you want to assemble and setup everything yourself, learning the most about your machine, just omit the notes at check-out - simple!

calibre_conversion:
Calibre Conversion on the RL 550C is both as quick and easy as you want to make it. Dillon offers various levels of convenience to suit your requirements and budget.

Option 1 - Minimum Kit   As a minimum, you will need the following to change calibres:
  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
  • Reloading Die Set for the specific calibre.

Adding a Case Gauge for the specific calibre is always a good idea! 
Option 2 - Convenient Conversion

Option 1 does not take full advantage of the convenience offered by the RL 550C’s interchangeable tool head. So, if you want to leave your dies pre-set, you'll need:

  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
  • Reloading Die Set for the specific calibre.
  • Dillon RL 550C Tool Head (DLN-13909)

Including an additional powder die allows you to move your powder measure from tool head to tool head without changing the flare or belling adjustment. Choose from:

  • Dillon Powder Die (DLN-20064)
  • Dillon Oversize Powder Die (DLN-21253) for calibres too large in diameter to fit into the standard powder die.

We call this 'Convenient Calibre Conversion', a.k.a. the moderately easy way. If you don't already have one, we always believe that a Case Gauge for the specific calibre would be a good idea! 
Option 3 - The Easy Way 

For the full Dillon convenience of changing calibres, consider the option to leave your dies and powder system set up and dedicated to a specific cartridge for faster, easier calibre changes. We call this 'Calibre Conversion, the Easy Way':

  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
  • Reloading Die Set for the specific calibre.
  • Dillon RL 550C Quick Change Kit (DLN-22058), which includes:
    • Dillon Powder Measure (DLN-20782)
    • Dillon Powder Die (DLN-20064)
    • Dillon RL 550C Tool Head (DLN-13909)
    • Dillon Toolhead Stand (DLN-22055)
  • Quick-change Dust Cover (DLN-11143) keeps the assembled tool head with powder measure dust free.
  • Case Gauge for the specific calibre (if available).

If you already have the optional electric case feeder you may need a different case feed plate. Please refer to the calibre conversion chart in the Instruction Manual for the correct plate. The RL 550 C Instruction Manual can be downloaded here, or call Shooting Stuff for advice. Available case feed plates (applicable to the RL 550 C) are:

  • Dillon Large Pistol Case Feed Plate (DLN-21072)
  • Dillon Small Pistol Case Feed Plate (DLN-21073)
key_features:
•  4-station, progressive reloading machine:
    • Station 1. Resize and deprime, seat a new primer
    • Station 2. Flare handgun cases, dispense propellant
    • Station 3. Seat the bullet
    • Station 4. Crimp the cartridge case
  • Insert cartridge cases manually.
  • Index the shell plate manually.
  • Feed and insert new primers automatically.
  • Dispense propellant automatically.
  • Operator places bullets manually.
  • Eject loaded cartridges automatically.
  • Loads most popular rifle and handgun calibres (requires additional calibre-specific items).
  • Accepts standard ⅞” x 14 tpi (thread per inch) dies. - Dillon dies are designed for high speed use, as well as rapid cleaning. Non-Dillon dies must re-size and de-prime in the same die. Note that the case flaring die from other brands is not used on the RL 550B, as this function is covered from the calibre conversion kit and powder die.
  • Interchangeable tool head, for quick and easy calibre conversion.

 While not absolutely essential when using carbide dies, we highly recommend Dillon's easy-to-apply, spray-on case lube. Trust us on this - you'll feel the difference!
  • Case Gauge
 Check each and every one of your 9mm cartridges for absolute confidence that none have high primers, none are cracked nor have other damage. If that sounds like too much effort just use the gauge occasionally to keep your reloading process in tune. Worth its weight in Stainless Steel!
  • Spare Parts Kit
 A collection of small parts that could easily get lost, or break, consider the Spare Parts Kit your insurance package until the Dillon Lifetime No-B.S. Warranty kicks in. After all, Murphy's Law states that if something can go wrong it will, and at the worst possible time (like the night before your match)
  • DVD Instruction Manual
 Video conveys so much more than printed pictures and text. You won't find this info on YouTube!
  • Setup

We will gladly setup your machine for you for FREE, as far as possible.

  • If you collect from us we can fully assemble the machine and included accessories, and then adjust the dies and powder charge.
  • If we ship the kit to you via courier, the extent of the setup is limited since we need to re-package the kit for safe shipping. We can install and adjust the dies, and set the powder charge, but you'll need to assemble all the bits.
