,product_weight=1,recommended_accesories=

Primer Transfer 

Dillon offers a manual system of flip tray and pick-up tubes or an automated system to get the primers from their shipping box into the RL 550 primer magazine. While the manual approach is most popular - that's why they're included with this kit - the RF 100 is really convenient! Consider this a reminder ...

  • RF 100 Automatic Primer Filler 
 The Dillon RF 100 Automatic Primer Filler is an electrically powered machine to sort and transfer a hundred primers from their packaging box into a "transfer tube", for subsequent transfer into the primer magazine of your favourite Dillon progressive reloading machine. The RF 100 eliminates the need to manually fill primer pick-up tubes, and is available for either large or small primers with conversion kits to change to the other size.
  • RF 100 for large primers, 220V (DLN-97112)
  • Conversion kit to load small primers (DLN-17903)
  • RF 100 for small primers, 220V (DLN-97113)
  • Conversion kit to load large primers (DLN-17902)
,required_accesories=

You will also need the following (not included with the machine) to reload:

  • Scale 

Set and periodically check your powder charge, we recommend one of the following: 

  • Dillon D-Terminator electronic scale (DLN-10483), and protective case (CED-SCase)
  • Dillon Eliminator balance-beam scale (DLN-13480)
  • CED Universal digital pocket scale (CED-UDPS)
  • Loading Manual
  • RDM’s Somchem reloading manual, version 2 (SomchemManual) is the only manual to include data for local, South African propellants.
  • DVD: Competition Reloading with Brian Enos (DLN-14341) - a step-by-step guide through the reloading process for IPSC, Steel Challenge and other action-shooting styles.
  • Safety Glasses 

You should always protect your eyes when reloading. Primers contain explosive compounds and nitrocellulose propellant is extremely flammable, with explosive characteristics when burning in a confined volume. We recommend:

  • Draeger X-pect safety glasses (Xpect) are made of tough, clear polycarbonate for indoor use, like reloading.
  • Rudy Project Rydon glasses (Rydon) are made of super-tough ImpactX material for superior protection, while reloading or when shooting. 
  • Vernier calliper 

Set and check cartridge dimensions, like crimp and overall length, we recommend:

  • CED digital calliper (CED-DigiCal). The calliper is not absolutely essential, but close enough that we included it here!

Ram diameter 1½” 
Loading rate
  • 400 to 600 rounds per hour,
  • 800 rounds per hour when using the optional 220V electric case feeder
Height (from bench)
  • without optional electric case feeder - 21" (~535mm) 
  • with electric case feeder installed - 38½" (~980mm) 
  • with optional strong mount - additional 9” (~220mm) 
Capacity
  • Small Powder Bar - throws from a little under 3 to about 20 grains of powder.
  • Large Powder Bar - throws from 15 to nearly 45 grains of extruded type propellant, and from 20 to about 50 grains of ball/spherical type propellant.

Additional Powder bars (not included with the machine):

  • Dillon Extra Small Powder Bar (DLN-20780) - throws from ½ to about 3 grains.
  • Dillon Magnum Rifle Powder Bar (DLN-21353) - throws up to ~73 grains of extruded type propellant and ~82 grains of ball/spherical type propellant. 

 

NOTE: Capacities depend on actual propellant type, the values listed here are approximate.

calibre_conversion:
Calibre Conversion on the RL 550C is both as quick and easy as you want to make it. Dillon offers various levels of convenience to suit your requirements and budget.

Option 1 - Minimum Kit   As a minimum, you will need the following to change calibres:
  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
  • Reloading Die Set for the specific calibre.

Adding a Case Gauge for the specific calibre is always a good idea! 
Option 2 - Convenient Conversion

Option 1 does not take full advantage of the convenience offered by the RL 550C’s interchangeable tool head. So, if you want to leave your dies pre-set, you'll need:

  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
  • Reloading Die Set for the specific calibre.
  • Dillon RL 550C Tool Head (DLN-13909)

Including an additional powder die allows you to move your powder measure from tool head to tool head without changing the flare or belling adjustment. Choose from:

  • Dillon Powder Die (DLN-20064)
  • Dillon Oversize Powder Die (DLN-21253) for calibres too large in diameter to fit into the standard powder die.

We call this 'Convenient Calibre Conversion', a.k.a. the moderately easy way. If you don't already have one, we always believe that a Case Gauge for the specific calibre would be a good idea! 
Option 3 - The Easy Way 

For the full Dillon convenience of changing calibres, consider the option to leave your dies and powder system set up and dedicated to a specific cartridge for faster, easier calibre changes. We call this 'Calibre Conversion, the Easy Way':

  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
  • Reloading Die Set for the specific calibre.
  • Dillon RL 550C Quick Change Kit (DLN-22058), which includes:
    • Dillon Powder Measure (DLN-20782)
    • Dillon Powder Die (DLN-20064)
    • Dillon RL 550C Tool Head (DLN-13909)
    • Dillon Toolhead Stand (DLN-22055)
  • Quick-change Dust Cover (DLN-11143) keeps the assembled tool head with powder measure dust free.
  • Case Gauge for the specific calibre (if available).

If you already have the optional electric case feeder you may need a different case feed plate. Please refer to the calibre conversion chart in the Instruction Manual for the correct plate. The RL 550 C Instruction Manual can be downloaded here, or call Shooting Stuff for advice. Available case feed plates (applicable to the RL 550 C) are:

  • Dillon Large Pistol Case Feed Plate (DLN-21072)
  • Dillon Small Pistol Case Feed Plate (DLN-21073)
key_features:
•  4-station, progressive reloading machine:
    • Station 1. Resize and deprime, seat a new primer
    • Station 2. Flare handgun cases, dispense propellant
    • Station 3. Seat the bullet
    • Station 4. Crimp the cartridge case
  • Insert cartridge cases manually.
  • Index the shell plate manually.
  • Feed and insert new primers automatically.
  • Dispense propellant automatically.
  • Operator places bullets manually.
  • Eject loaded cartridges automatically.
  • Loads most popular rifle and handgun calibres (requires additional calibre-specific items).
  • Accepts standard ⅞” x 14 tpi (thread per inch) dies. - Dillon dies are designed for high speed use, as well as rapid cleaning. Non-Dillon dies must re-size and de-prime in the same die. Note that the case flaring die from other brands is not used on the RL 550B, as this function is covered from the calibre conversion kit and powder die.
  • Interchangeable tool head, for quick and easy calibre conversion.

description:

For complete peace of mind, the RL 550 is covered by Dillon’s legendary Lifetime "No-B.S." warranty. All electrical & electronic components in Dillon equipment are covered by a one-year warranty, as are textiles. Shooting Stuff fully supports Dillon’s warranty and has a spares cupboard with most spare parts available in stock. 

Click here to review a full description of the RL 550 and the many available options.
package_contents:
Shooting Stuff's Senisible Minimum RL 550 system comprises the following:

  • RL 550B machine
 This is "the big white box" that includes the main reloading machine with the tool head and primer system already fitted and 
  • Calibre Conversion Kit Box, with calibre-specific parts for 9mm Luger
  • Primer early warning system
  • Operating handle, with knob
  • Powder measure
  • RL 550 Accessory Bag
  • RL 550 Accessory Box
  • Printed Instruction Manual
  • Dillon 9mm Carbide Die Set

3-die set for progressive relaoding machines:

  • Carbide sizing die with decapping assembly
  • Bullet seating die
  • Separate taper crimp die
  • Shooting Stuff 1-inch spanner
 The Shooting Stuff Spanner (1-inch) is compact enough to allow operation within the close confines of the tool heads and fits the 1" lock-nuts supplied with all current generation Dillon dies. The smaller closed ring fits the 7/16" powder measure adjustment bolt, and others.
  • Primer Flip Tray
 Dillon's metal flip tray is used to quickly get primers "the right way up" after dispensing these from their tray.
  • Case lube
 While not absolutely essential when using carbide dies, we highly recommend Dillon's easy-to-apply, spray-on case lube. Trust us on this - you'll feel the difference!
  • Case Gauge
 Check each and every one of your 9mm cartridges for absolute confidence that none have high primers, none are cracked nor have other damage. If that sounds like too much effort just use the gauge occasionally to keep your reloading process in tune. Worth its weight in Stainless Steel!
  • Setup

We will gladly setup your machine for you for FREE, as far as possible.

  • If you collect from us we can fully assemble the machine and included accessories, and then adjust the dies and powder charge.
  • If we ship the kit to you via courier, the extent of the setup is limited since we need to re-package the kit for safe shipping. We can install and adjust the dies, and set the powder charge, but you'll need to assemble all the bits.

 

Please make notes when checking out & finalising your purchase that include your load details, or send us an e-mail once your order is confirmed. If you want to assemble and setup everything yourself, learning the most about your machine, just omit the notes at check-out - simple!

name: Dillon SL 900 Comprehensive Setup for 12 Gauge
description:
The Dillon SL 900 Comprehensive Setup for 12 gauge is a progressive reloader capable of loading 600 to 800 rounds of 12ga shotgun ammo per hour. Shooting Stuff has included all the options and safety features for the SL 900 – this is the "Full Monty"!

The Dillon SL 900 has been designed to reliably load shot with a diameter smaller than #5; 3.1mm. It is important to ensure that your shot is properly spherical, uniform in size and adequately lubricated with graphite powder.

For complete peace of mind, the SL 900 is covered by Dillon’s legendary Lifetime "No-B.S." warranty. All electrical & electronic components in Dillon equipment are covered by a one-year warranty, as are textiles. Shooting Stuff fully supports Dillon’s warranty and has a spares cupboard with most spare parts available in stock. 

Click here to review a full description of the SL 900 and the many available options.

meta_description: Looking for Dillon SL 900 Comprehensive Setup for 12 Gauge? Shooting Stuff has a large range of shooting products and accessories. Buy online today!
calibre_conversion:
Shooting Stuff has pre-configured this package for you for just one calibre, 12 Gauge. Your Dillon SL 900 can load 20 and 28 Gauge calibres. Calibre Conversion on the SL 900 is both as quick and easy as you want to make it. Dillon offers various levels of convenience to suit your requirements and budget. 

Option 1 - Minimum Kit 

As a minimum, you will need the following to change calibres:

  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
Option 2 - Convenient Conversion

Option 1 does not take full advantage of the convenience offered by the SL 900's interchangeable tool head. So, if you want to leave your dies pre-set, you'll need:

  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.

Depending on what calibre you are going to, and where you are changing from, you may also need a different case feed plate for the electric case feeder. Please refer to the calibre conversion chart in the Instruction Manual for the correct plate. The SL 900 Instruction Manual can be downloaded here, or call Shooting Stuff for advice. Available case feed plates (applicable to the SL 900) are:

  • 12 Gauge Casefeed plate (DLN-17811)
  • 20/28 Gauge Casefeed plate (DLN-97045)
We call this “calibre conversion, the moderately easy way” and believe that a case gauge for the specific calibre would be a good idea!
Option 3 - The Easy Way 

For the full Dillon convenience of changing calibres “the easy way” consider the option to leave your dies, powder system and powder check system set up and dedicated to a specific cartridge for faster, easier calibre changes. We call this “calibre conversion, the easy way”

  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
  • Tool head stand (DLN-22055)
  • Quick-change Dust Cover (DLN-11143) keeps the assembled tool head with powder measure dust free.

Depending on what calibre you are going to, and where you are changing from, you may also need a different case feed plate for the electric case feeder. Please refer to the calibre conversion chart in the Instruction Manual for the correct plate. The SL 900 Instruction Manual can be downloaded here, or call Shooting Stuff for advice. Available case feed plates (applicable to the SL 900) are:

  • 12 Gauge Casefeed plate (DLN-17811)
  • 20/28 Gauge Casefeed plate (DLN-97045)
key_features:
• The SL 900 is a 5-station, progressive reloading machine:
    • Station 1: Insert hull into shell plate (at the bottom), resize and de-prime (at the top)
    • Station 2: Seat a new primer (at the bottom) and dispense propellant (at the top)
    • Station 3: Insert plastic wad into hull (at the bottom) and dispense shot (at the top)
    • Station 4: Hull is formed and folded (at the top)
    • Station 5: Final crimp and seating closing the top (at the top)
  • Insert hull automatically.
  • Index the shell plate automatically.
  • Feed and insert new primers automatically.
  • Dispense propellant automatically.
  • Operator places wads manually.
  • Eject loaded shot shells automatically.
  • Setup for 12 gauge, but can load 20 and 28 gauge calibres (requires additional calibre-specific items).
  • Interchangeable tool head, for easy calibre conversion.
optional_accesories: Click here for a comprehensive list of optional accessories
package_contents:
Shooting Stuff's comprehensive SL 900 system comprises the following:

  • SL 900 Machine
 This is "the big white box" that includes the main reloading machine and 
  • SL 900 tool head and frame with calibre-specific parts for 12 Gauge
  • Operating handle
  • Powder measure
  • Shot dispenser
  • Shotshell chute
  • SL 900 hardware bag
  • SL 900 accessory bag
  • Case feed mounting post and Case Feed Tube
  • Shot hopper post and hopper
  • Printed Instruction Manual
  • SL 900 Strong Mount
  • Loaded cartridge bin (blue, plastic AkroBin)
  • SL 900 Case Feeder
 220V electric case feeder with a case feeder plate. True convenience!
  • Low Powder Sensor
 This is a warning system that provides an audible and visual reminder when it's time to refill your powder reservoir.
  • Toolkit
 Shooting Stuff's Toolkit for the SL900 is a stylish, one-piece bracket that mounts to the "blue" Dillon progressive reloading machines to organise and store a set of ball-ended Allen wrenches and the 1-inch spanner.
  • Smooth-glide Roller Handle
 Shooting Stuff's roller handle runs on sealed bearings for enhanced reloading comfort and tactile feedback when seating primers.
  • SL900 Machine Cover
 The Shooting Stuff SL 900 Machine Cover is perfect for keeping your equipment clean and free of dust, when not in use.This cover is suitable for the Dillon XL 650, Super 1050 and SL900 progressive reloading machines.
  • Spare Parts Kit
 A collection of small parts that could easily get lost, or break, consider the Spare Parts Kit your insurance package until the Dillon Lifetime No-B.S. Warranty kicks in. After all, Murphy's Law states that if something can go wrong it will, and at the worst possible time (like the night before your match)
  • Setup

We will gladly setup your machine for you for FREE, as far as possible.

  • If you collect from us we can fully assemble the machine and included accessories, and then adjust the dies and powder charge.
  • If we ship the kit to you via courier, the extent of the setup is limited since we need to re-package the kit for safe shipping. We can install and adjust the dies, and set the powder charge, but you'll need to assemble all the bits.

Please add notes when checking out & finalising your purchase that include your load details, or send us an e-mail once your order is confirmed. If you want to assemble and setup everything yourself, learning the most about your machine, just omit the notes at check-out - simple!
required_accesories:
You will also need the following items (not included with this kit) to reload:

  • Scale 

Set and periodically check your powder charge, we recommend one of the following: 

  • Dillon D-Terminator electronic scale (DLN-10483), and protective case (CED-SCase)
  • Dillon Eliminator balance-beam scale (DLN-13480)
  • CED Universal digital pocket scale (CED-UDPS)
  • Loading Manual
  • RDM’s Somchem reloading manual, version 2 (SomchemManual) is the only manual to include data for local, South African propellants.
  • Safety Glasses 

You should always protect your eyes when reloading. Primers contain explosive compounds and nitrocellulose propellant is extremely flammable, with explosive characteristics when burning in a confined volume. We recommend:

  • Draeger X-pect safety glasses (Xpect) are made of tough, clear polycarbonate for indoor use, like reloading.
  • Rudy Project Rydon glasses (Rydon) are made of super-tough ImpactX material for superior protection, while reloading or when shooting. 
  • Vernier calliper 

Set and check cartridge dimensions, like crimp and overall length, we recommend:

  • CED digital calliper (CED-DigiCal). The calliper is not absolutely essential, but close enough that we included it here!

Capacity
  • Large Powder Bar - throws from 15 to nearly 45 grains of extruded type propellant, and from 20 to about 50 grains of ball/spherical type propellant.
  • Standard shot bar - thows 1 1/4 oz of lead shot
  • Small gauge shot bar - thows 1/2-1 oz of  lead shot
NOTE: Capacities depend on actual propellant type, the values listed here are approximate.

 Check each and every one of your 9mm cartridges for absolute confidence that none have high primers, none are cracked nor have other damage. If that sounds like too much effort just use the gauge occasionally to keep your reloading process in tune. Worth its weight in Stainless Steel!
  • Spare Parts Kit
 A collection of small parts that could easily get lost, or break, consider the Spare Parts Kit your insurance package until the Dillon Lifetime No-B.S. Warranty kicks in. After all, Murphy's Law states that if something can go wrong it will, and at the worst possible time (like the night before your match)
  • Setup

We will gladly setup your machine for you for FREE, as far as possible.

  • If you collect from us we can fully assemble the machine and included accessories, and then adjust the dies and powder charge.
  • If we ship the kit to you via courier, the extent of the setup is limited since we need to re-package the kit for safe shipping. We can install and adjust the dies, and set the powder charge, but you'll need to assemble all the bits.

 

Please make notes when checking out & finalising your purchase that include your load details, or send us an e-mail once your order is confirmed. If you want to assemble and setup everything yourself, learning the most about your machine, just omit the notes at check-out - simple!

name: Dillon Super 1050 Comprehensive Setup for 9mm Luger
description:
The Dillon Super 1050 Comprehensive Setup for 9mm Luger is a progressive reloader capable of loading 1 000 to 1 200 rounds of 9mm ammunition per hour. Shooting Stuff has included all the options and safety features, all the things that make the Super 1050 – well, super! Barring the autodrive and bullet feeder, this is the "Full Monty"!

The Super 1050, a commercial system engineered to load hundreds of thousands of rounds, is covered by a 1-year warranty. All electrical & electronic components in Dillon equipment are covered by a one-year warranty, as are textiles. Shooting Stuff fully supports Dillon’s warranty and has a spares cupboard with most spare parts available in stock. 

Click here to review a full description of the Super 1050 and the many available options.

calibre_conversion:
Calibre Conversion on the Super 1050 is both as quick and easy as you want to make it. Dillon offers various levels of convenience to suit your requirements and budget.

Option 1 - Minimum Kit 

As a minimum, you will need the following to change calibres:

  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
  • Reloading Die Set for the specific calibre.

Adding a Case Gauge for the specific calibre is always a good idea! 
Option 2 - Convenient Conversion

Option 1 does not take full advantage of the convenience offered by the Super 1050’s interchangeable tool head. So, if you want to leave your dies pre-set, you'll need:

  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
  • Reloading Die Set for the specific calibre.
  • Dillon Super 1050 Tool head (DLN-20420)

Including an additional Dillon Powder Die (DLN-20064) allows you to move your powder measure from tool head to tool head without changing the flare or belling adjustment. Consider taking a second powder die to also share the powder check system.

We call this “calibre conversion, the moderately easy way” and believe that a case gauge for the specific calibre would be a good idea!
Option 3 - The Easy Way  For the full Dillon convenience of changing calibres “the easy way” consider the option to leave your dies, powder system and powder check system set up and dedicated to a specific cartridge for faster, easier calibre changes. We call this “calibre conversion, the easy way”
  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
  • Reloading Die Set for the specific calibre.
  • Super 1050 Quick Change Kit (DLN-21393),which includes
    • Powder measure (DLN-20421),
    • Powder die (DLN-20064),
    • Tool head (DLN-20420),
  • Dillon Super 1050 Tool head stand - Blue (DLN-62200), or Black (DLN-62201).
  • Quick-change Dust Cover (DLN-11143) keeps the assembled tool head with powder measure dust free.
  • Case Gauge for the specific calibre (if available).

You may also need a different case feed plate for the electric case feeder. Please refer to the calibre conversion chart in the Instruction Manual for the correct plate. The Super 1050 Instruction Manual can be downloaded here, or call Shooting Stuff for advice. Available case feed plates (applicable to the Super 1050) are:

  • Large pistol (DLN-21072)
  • Small pistol (DLN-21073)
  • Small rifle (DLN-21074)
  • Large rifle (DLN-21075)
key_features:
• 8-station, progressive reloading machine:
    • Station 1: Insert case into shell plate
    • Station 2: Resize and de-prime
    • Station 3: Swage primer pocket
    • Station 4: Seat a new primer
    • Station 5: Dispense propellant
    • Station 6: Powder check
    • Station 7: Seat the bullet
    • Station 8: Crimp the cartridge case
  • Insert cartridge cases automatically.
  • Index the shell plate automatically.
  • Feed and insert new primers automatically.
  • Dispense propellant automatically.
  • Check propellant level (for safety) in each and every case automatically.
  • Operator places bullets manually.
  • Eject loaded cartridges automatically.
  • Loads most popular handgun calibres and several rifle calibres (requires additional calibre-specific items).
  • Accepts standard ⅞” x 14 tpi (thread per inch) dies. Dillon dies are designed for high speed use, as well as rapid cleaning. Non-Dillon dies must re-size and de-prime in the same die. Note that the case flaring die from other brands is not used on the Super 1050, as this function is covered from the calibre conversion kit and powder die.
  • Interchangeable tool head, for easy calibre conversion.

package_contents:
Shooting Stuff's comprehensive Super 1050 system comprises the following:

 

  • Super 1050 machine
 This is "the big white box" – OK, the 1050 comes in a brown box, that includes the main reloading machine and
  • Calibre Conversion Box
  • 9mm Luger Die Box
  • Primer early warning system
  • Case Feed Tube
  • Case Feed Mounting Post
  • Operating Handle
  • 1050 Accessory Box
  • 1050 Tube Bag
  • Printed instruction manual
  • Case Feed Assembly 
 220V electric case feeder with a small-pistol case feeder plate. True convenience!
  • Powder Check System
 Once properly adjusted, this sensor verifies a safe charge in each and every case during the loading process.
  • Bullet Tray Kit
 Dillon's cast Bullet Tray mounts to the left plate of the machine mount, and holds a few hundred bullets conveniently close to where they're needed.
  • Toolholder with wrech set
 The Dillon Toolholder with Wrench Set is a bracket that mounts to the Super 1050 progressive reloading machine to organise and store a set of dipped, ball-ended Allen wrenches and the 1" Bench Wrench included in the kit.
  • Smooth-glide Roller Handle
 Shooting Stuff's roller handle runs on sealed bearings for enhanced reloading comfort and tactile feedback when seating primers.
  • Machine Cover
 The Shooting Stuff Super 1050 Machine Cover is perfect for keeping your equipment clean and free of dust, when not in use.This cover is suitable for the Dillon XL 650, Super 1050 and SL900 progressive reloading machines.
  • Primer Flip Tray
 Dillon's metal flip tray is used to quickly get primers "the right way up" after dispensing these from their tray. 
  • Primer Pick-up Tubes
 A pack of 4 additional primer pick-up tubes used to pick-up small primers from the Flip Tray. Together with the one included with the reloading machine you'll be able to pre-fill 500 primers so that you can conveniently load a substantail batch of ammo with minimum interuption to replenish components.
  • Case lube
 While not absolutely essential when using carbide dies, we highly recommend Dillon's easy-to-apply, spray-on case lube. Trust us on this - you'll feel the difference!
  • Case Gauge
 Check each and every one of your 9mm cartridges for absolute confidence that none have high primers, none are cracked nor have other damage. If that sounds like too much effort just use the gauge occasionally to keep your reloading process in tune. Worth its weight in Stainless Steel!
  • Spare Parts Kit
 A collection of small parts that could easily get lost, or break, consider the Spare Parts Kit your insurance package until the Dillon Lifetime No-B.S. Warranty kicks in. After all, Murphy's Law states that if something can go wrong it will, and at the worst possible time (like the night before your match)
  • DVD Instruction Manual
 Video conveys so much more than printed pictures and text. You won't find this info on YouTube!
  • Setup

We will gladly setup your machine for you for FREE, as far as possible.

  • If you collect from us we can fully assemble the machine and included accessories, and then adjust the dies and powder charge.
  • If we ship the kit to you via courier, the extent of the setup is limited since we need to re-package the kit for safe shipping. We can install and adjust the dies, and set the powder charge, but you'll need to assemble all the bits.

 

Please make notes when checking out & finalising your purchase that include your load details, or send us an e-mail once your order is confirmed. If you want to assemble and setup everything yourself, learning the most about your machine, just omit the notes at check-out - simple!
recommended_accesories:
Primer Transfer 

Dillon offers a manual system of flip tray and pick-up tubes or an automated system to get the primers from their shipping box into the Super 1050 primer magazine. While the manual approach is most popular - that's why they're included with this kit - the RF 100 is really convenient! Consider this a reminder ...

  • RF 100 Automatic Primer Filler 
 The Dillon RF 100 Automatic Primer Filler is an electrically powered machine to sort and transfer a hundred primers from their packaging box into a "transfer tube", for subsequent transfer into the primer magazine of your favourite Dillon progressive reloading machine. The RF 100 eliminates the need to manually fill primer pick-up tubes, and is available for either large or small primers with conversion kits to change to the other size.
  • RF 100 for large primers, 220V (DLN-97112)
  • Conversion kit to load small primers (DLN-17903)
  • RF 100 for small primers, 220V (DLN-97113)
  • Conversion kit to load large primers (DLN-17902)
required_accesories:
Other than the basic machine which includes a calibre conversion kit, a set of dies and the electric case feeder, we suggest you will also need the following items:

  •  Scale 
  Set and periodically check your powder charge, we recommend one of the following: 
  • Dillon D-Terminator electronic scale (DLN-10483), and protective case (CED-SCase)
  • Dillon Eliminator balance-beam scale (DLN-13480)
  • CED Universal digital pocket scale (CED-UDPS)
  • Loading Manual
  • RDM’s Somchem reloading manual, version 2 (SomchemManual) is the only manual to include data for local, South African propellants.
  • DVD: Competition Reloading with Brian Enos (DLN-14341) - a step-by-step guide through the reloading process for IPSC, Steel Challenge and other action-shooting styles.
  • Safety Glasses 

You should always protect your eyes when reloading. Primers contain explosive compounds and nitrocellulose propellant is extremely flammable, with explosive characteristics when burning in a confined volume. We recommend:

  • Draeger X-pect safety glasses (Xpect) are made of tough, clear polycarbonate for indoor use, like reloading.
  • Rudy Project Rydon glasses (Rydon) are made of super-tough ImpactX material for superior protection, while reloading or when shooting. 
  • Vernier calliper 

Set and check cartridge dimensions, like crimp and overall length, we recommend:

  • CED digital calliper (CED-DigiCal). The calliper is not absolutely essential, but close enough that we included it here!
technical_specifications:
Ram diameter 1½” 
Loading rate
  • 1 000 to 1 200 rounds per hour
Height (from bench)
  • 38" (~960mm) with the electric case feeder installed.
Capacity
  • Extra Small Powder Bar -  throws from ½ grain to about 3 grains
  • Small Powder Bar - throws from a little under 3 grains to about 20 grains of powder.
  • Large Powder Bar - throws from around 15 grains to nearly 45 grains of extruded type propellant, and from around 20 to about 50 grains of ball/spherical type propellant.
  • Magnum Powder Bar - throws up to ~73 grains of extruded type propellant and ~82 grains of ball/spherical type propellant (not generally required for the Super 1050). 

NOTE: Capacities depend on actual propellant type, the values listed here are approximate.

 Check each and every one of your 9mm cartridges for absolute confidence that none have high primers, none are cracked nor have other damage. If that sounds like too much effort just use the gauge occasionally to keep your reloading process in tune. Worth its weight in Stainless Steel!
  • Spare Parts Kit
 A collection of small parts that could easily get lost, or break, consider the Spare Parts Kit your insurance package until the Dillon Lifetime No-B.S. Warranty kicks in. After all, Murphy's Law states that if something can go wrong it will, and at the worst possible time (like the night before your match)
  • DVD Instruction Manual
 Video conveys so much more than printed pictures and text. You won't find this info on YouTube!
  • Setup

We will gladly setup your machine for you for FREE, as far as possible.

  • If you collect from us we can fully assemble the machine and included accessories, and then adjust the dies and powder charge.
  • If we ship the kit to you via courier, the extent of the setup is limited since we need to re-package the kit for safe shipping. We can install and adjust the dies, and set the powder charge, but you'll need to assemble all the bits.

 

Please make notes when checking out & finalising your purchase that include your load details, or send us an e-mail once your order is confirmed. If you want to assemble and setup everything yourself, learning the most about your machine, just omit the notes at check-out - simple!

description:
The Dillon Super 1050 Recommended Setup for 9mm Luger is a progressive reloader capable of loading 1 000 to 1 200 rounds of 9mm ammunition per hour. Shooting Stuff has included the most popular options and safety features, the things that make the Super 1050 – well, super!

The Super 1050, a commercial system engineered to load hundreds of thousands of rounds, is covered by a 1-year warranty. All electrical & electronic components in Dillon equipment are covered by a one-year warranty, as are textiles. Shooting Stuff fully supports Dillon’s warranty and has a spares cupboard with most spare parts available in stock.

calibre_conversion:
Calibre Conversion on the Super 1050 is both as quick and easy as you want to make it. Dillon offers various levels of convenience to suit your requirements and budget.

Option 1 - Minimum Kit 

As a minimum, you will need the following to change calibres:

  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
  • Reloading Die Set for the specific calibre.

Adding a Case Gauge for the specific calibre is always a good idea! 
Option 2 - Convenient Conversion

Option 1 does not take full advantage of the convenience offered by the Super 1050’s interchangeable tool head. So, if you want to leave your dies pre-set, you'll need:

  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
  • Reloading Die Set for the specific calibre.
  • Dillon Super 1050 Tool head (DLN-20420)

Including an additional Dillon Powder Die (DLN-20064) allows you to move your powder measure from tool head to tool head without changing the flare or belling adjustment. Consider taking a second powder die to also share the powder check system.

We call this “calibre conversion, the moderately easy way” and believe that a case gauge for the specific calibre would be a good idea!
Option 3 - The Easy Way  For the full Dillon convenience of changing calibres “the easy way” consider the option to leave your dies, powder system and powder check system set up and dedicated to a specific cartridge for faster, easier calibre changes. We call this “calibre conversion, the easy way”
  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
  • Reloading Die Set for the specific calibre.
  • Super 1050 Quick Change Kit (DLN-21393),which includes
    • Powder measure (DLN-20421),
    • Powder die (DLN-20064),
    • Tool head (DLN-20420),
  • Dillon Super 1050 Tool head stand - Blue (DLN-62200), or Black (DLN-62201).
  • Quick-change Dust Cover (DLN-11143) keeps the assembled tool head with powder measure dust free.
  • Case Gauge for the specific calibre (if available).

You may also need a different case feed plate for the electric case feeder. Please refer to the calibre conversion chart in the Instruction Manual for the correct plate. The Super 1050 Instruction Manual can be downloaded here, or call Shooting Stuff for advice. Available case feed plates (applicable to the Super 1050) are:

  • Large pistol (DLN-21072)
  • Small pistol (DLN-21073)
  • Small rifle (DLN-21074)
  • Large rifle (DLN-21075)
key_features:
• 8-station, progressive reloading machine:
    • Station 1: Insert case into shell plate
    • Station 2: Resize and de-prime
    • Station 3: Swage primer pocket
    • Station 4: Seat a new primer
    • Station 5: Dispense propellant
    • Station 6: Powder check
    • Station 7: Seat the bullet
    • Station 8: Crimp the cartridge case
  • Insert cartridge cases automatically.
  • Index the shell plate automatically.
  • Feed and insert new primers automatically.
  • Dispense propellant automatically.
  • Check propellant level (for safety) in each and every case automatically.
  • Operator places bullets manually.
  • Eject loaded cartridges automatically.
  • Loads most popular handgun calibres and several rifle calibres (requires additional calibre-specific items).
  • Accepts standard ⅞” x 14 tpi (thread per inch) dies. Dillon dies are designed for high speed use, as well as rapid cleaning. Non-Dillon dies must re-size and de-prime in the same die. Note that the case flaring die from other brands is not used on the Super 1050, as this function is covered from the calibre conversion kit and powder die.
  • Interchangeable tool head, for easy calibre conversion.

package_contents:
Shooting Stuff's recommended Super 1050 system comprises the following:

 

  • Super 1050 machine
 This is "the big white box" – OK, the 1050 comes in a brown box, that includes the main reloading machine and
  • Calibre Conversion Box
  • 9mm Luger Die Box
  • Primer early warning system
  • Case Feed Tube
  • Case Feed Mounting Post
  • Operating Handle
  • 1050 Accessory Box
  • 1050 Tube Bag
  • Printed instruction manual
  • Case Feed Assembly 
 220V electric case feeder with a small-pistol case feeder plate. True convenience!
  • Powder Check System
 Once properly adjusted, this sensor verifies a safe charge in each and every case during the loading process.
  • Bullet Tray Kit
 Dillon's cast Bullet Tray mounts to the left plate of the machine mount, and holds a few hundred bullets conveniently close to where they're needed.
  • Toolholder with wrech set
 The Dillon Toolholder with Wrench Set is a bracket that mounts to the Super 1050 progressive reloading machine to organise and store a set of dipped, ball-ended Allen wrenches and the 1" Bench Wrench included in the kit.
  • Primer Flip Tray
 Dillon's metal flip tray is used to quickly get primers "the right way up" after dispensing these from their tray. 
  • Primer Pick-up Tubes
 A pack of 4 additional primer pick-up tubes used to pick-up small primers from the Flip Tray. Together with the one included with the reloading machine you'll be able to pre-fill 500 primers so that you can conveniently load a substantail batch of ammo with minimum interuption to replenish components.
  • Case lube
 While not absolutely essential when using carbide dies, we highly recommend Dillon's easy-to-apply, spray-on case lube. Trust us on this - you'll feel the difference!

 Check each and every one of your 9mm cartridges for absolute confidence that none have high primers, none are cracked nor have other damage. If that sounds like too much effort just use the gauge occasionally to keep your reloading process in tune. Worth its weight in Stainless Steel!

recommended_accesories:
Primer Transfer 

Dillon offers a manual system of flip tray and pick-up tubes or an automated system to get the primers from their shipping box into the Super 1050 primer magazine. While the manual approach is most popular - that's why they're included with this kit - the RF 100 is really convenient! Consider this a reminder ...

  • RF 100 Automatic Primer Filler 
 The Dillon RF 100 Automatic Primer Filler is an electrically powered machine to sort and transfer a hundred primers from their packaging box into a "transfer tube", for subsequent transfer into the primer magazine of your favourite Dillon progressive reloading machine. The RF 100 eliminates the need to manually fill primer pick-up tubes, and is available for either large or small primers with conversion kits to change to the other size.
  • RF 100 for large primers, 220V (DLN-97112)
  • Conversion kit to load small primers (DLN-17903)
  • RF 100 for small primers, 220V (DLN-97113)
  • Conversion kit to load large primers (DLN-17902)
required_accesories:
Other than the basic machine which includes a calibre conversion kit, a set of dies and the electric case feeder, we suggest you will also need the following items:

  •  Scale 
  Set and periodically check your powder charge, we recommend one of the following: 
  • Dillon D-Terminator electronic scale (DLN-10483), and protective case (CED-SCase)
  • Dillon Eliminator balance-beam scale (DLN-13480)
  • CED Universal digital pocket scale (CED-UDPS)
  • Loading Manual
  • RDM’s Somchem reloading manual, version 2 (SomchemManual) is the only manual to include data for local, South African propellants.
  • DVD: Competition Reloading with Brian Enos (DLN-14341) - a step-by-step guide through the reloading process for IPSC, Steel Challenge and other action-shooting styles.
  • Safety Glasses 

You should always protect your eyes when reloading. Primers contain explosive compounds and nitrocellulose propellant is extremely flammable, with explosive characteristics when burning in a confined volume. We recommend:

  • Draeger X-pect safety glasses (Xpect) are made of tough, clear polycarbonate for indoor use, like reloading.
  • Rudy Project Rydon glasses (Rydon) are made of super-tough ImpactX material for superior protection, while reloading or when shooting. 
  • Vernier calliper 

Set and check cartridge dimensions, like crimp and overall length, we recommend:

  • CED digital calliper (CED-DigiCal). The calliper is not absolutely essential, but close enough that we included it here!
technical_specifications:
Ram diameter 1½” 
Loading rate
  • 1 000 to 1 200 rounds per hour
Height (from bench)
  • 38" (~960mm) with the electric case feeder installed.
Capacity
  • Extra Small Powder Bar -  throws from ½ grain to about 3 grains
  • Small Powder Bar - throws from a little under 3 grains to about 20 grains of powder.
  • Large Powder Bar - throws from around 15 grains to nearly 45 grains of extruded type propellant, and from around 20 to about 50 grains of ball/spherical type propellant.
  • Magnum Powder Bar - throws up to ~73 grains of extruded type propellant and ~82 grains of ball/spherical type propellant (not generally required for the Super 1050). 

NOTE: Capacities depend on actual propellant type, the values listed here are approximate.

name: Dillon Super 1050 Sensible Minimum Setup for 9mm Luger
description:
The Dillon Super 1050 Sensible Minimum Setup for 9mm Luger is a progressive reloader capable of loading 1 000 to 1 200 rounds of 9mm ammunition per hour. Shooting Stuff has included the most essential options to enable you to start loading on the Super 1050.

The Super 1050, a commercial system engineered to load hundreds of thousands of rounds, is covered by a 1-year warranty. All electrical & electronic components in Dillon equipment are covered by a one-year warranty, as are textiles. Shooting Stuff fully supports Dillon’s warranty and has a spares cupboard with most spare parts available in stock. 

Click here to review a full description of the Super 1050 and the many available options.

calibre_conversion:
Calibre Conversion on the Super 1050 is both as quick and easy as you want to make it. Dillon offers various levels of convenience to suit your requirements and budget.

Option 1 - Minimum Kit 

As a minimum, you will need the following to change calibres:

  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
  • Reloading Die Set for the specific calibre.

Adding a Case Gauge for the specific calibre is always a good idea! 
Option 2 - Convenient Conversion

Option 1 does not take full advantage of the convenience offered by the Super 1050’s interchangeable tool head. So, if you want to leave your dies pre-set, you'll need:

  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
  • Reloading Die Set for the specific calibre.
  • Dillon Super 1050 Tool head (DLN-20420)

Including an additional Dillon Powder Die (DLN-20064) allows you to move your powder measure from tool head to tool head without changing the flare or belling adjustment. Consider taking a second powder die to also share the powder check system.

We call this “calibre conversion, the moderately easy way” and believe that a case gauge for the specific calibre would be a good idea!
Option 3 - The Easy Way  For the full Dillon convenience of changing calibres “the easy way” consider the option to leave your dies, powder system and powder check system set up and dedicated to a specific cartridge for faster, easier calibre changes. We call this “calibre conversion, the easy way”
  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
  • Reloading Die Set for the specific calibre.
  • Super 1050 Quick Change Kit (DLN-21393),which includes
    • Powder measure (DLN-20421),
    • Powder die (DLN-20064),
    • Tool head (DLN-20420),
  • Dillon Super 1050 Tool head stand - Blue (DLN-62200), or Black (DLN-62201).
  • Quick-change Dust Cover (DLN-11143) keeps the assembled tool head with powder measure dust free.
  • Case Gauge for the specific calibre (if available).

You may also need a different case feed plate for the electric case feeder. Please refer to the calibre conversion chart in the Instruction Manual for the correct plate. The Super 1050 Instruction Manual can be downloaded here, or call Shooting Stuff for advice. Available case feed plates (applicable to the Super 1050) are:

  • Large pistol (DLN-21072)
  • Small pistol (DLN-21073)
  • Small rifle (DLN-21074)
  • Large rifle (DLN-21075)
key_features:
• 8-station, progressive reloading machine:
    • Station 1: Insert case into shell plate
    • Station 2: Resize and de-prime
    • Station 3: Swage primer pocket
    • Station 4: Seat a new primer
    • Station 5: Dispense propellant
    • Station 6: Powder check
    • Station 7: Seat the bullet
    • Station 8: Crimp the cartridge case
  • Insert cartridge cases automatically.
  • Index the shell plate automatically.
  • Feed and insert new primers automatically.
  • Dispense propellant automatically.
  • Check propellant level (for safety) in each and every case automatically.
  • Operator places bullets manually.
  • Eject loaded cartridges automatically.
  • Loads most popular handgun calibres and several rifle calibres (requires additional calibre-specific items).
  • Accepts standard ⅞” x 14 tpi (thread per inch) dies. Dillon dies are designed for high speed use, as well as rapid cleaning. Non-Dillon dies must re-size and de-prime in the same die. Note that the case flaring die from other brands is not used on the Super 1050, as this function is covered from the calibre conversion kit and powder die.
  • Interchangeable tool head, for easy calibre conversion.

package_contents:
Shooting Stuff's sensible minimum Super 1050 system comprises the following:

 

  • Super 1050 machine
 This is "the big white box" – OK, the 1050 comes in a brown box, that includes the main reloading machine and
  • Calibre Conversion Box
  • 9mm Luger Die Box
  • Primer early warning system
  • Case Feed Tube
  • Case Feed Mounting Post
  • Operating Handle
  • 1050 Accessory Box
  • 1050 Tube Bag
  • Printed instruction manual
  • Case Feed Assembly 
 220V electric case feeder with a small-pistol case feeder plate. True convenience!
  • Powder Check System
 Once properly adjusted, this sensor verifies a safe charge in each and every case during the loading process.
  • 1" Spanner
 Shooting Stuff's 1-inch spanner gets in to the small space available on the tool head so that you can adjust the dies as required. Conventional spanners and shifters are just too bulky!
  • Primer Flip Tray
 Dillon's metal flip tray is used to quickly get primers "the right way up" after dispensing these from their tray. 
  • Case lube
 While not absolutely essential when using carbide dies, we highly recommend Dillon's easy-to-apply, spray-on case lube. Trust us on this - you'll feel the difference!
  • Case Gauge
 Check each and every one of your 9mm cartridges for absolute confidence that none have high primers, none are cracked nor have other damage. If that sounds like too much effort just use the gauge occasionally to keep your reloading process in tune. Worth its weight in Stainless Steel!
  • Setup

We will gladly setup your machine for you for FREE, as far as possible.

  • If you collect from us we can fully assemble the machine and included accessories, and then adjust the dies and powder charge.
  • If we ship the kit to you via courier, the extent of the setup is limited since we need to re-package the kit for safe shipping. We can install and adjust the dies, and set the powder charge, but you'll need to assemble all the bits.

 

Please make notes when checking out & finalising your purchase that include your load details, or send us an e-mail once your order is confirmed. If you want to assemble and setup everything yourself, learning the most about your machine, just omit the notes at check-out - simple!
recommended_accesories: Click here for a comprehensive list of recommended accessories
required_accesories:
Other than the basic machine which includes a calibre conversion kit, a set of dies and the electric case feeder, we suggest you will also need the following items:

  •  Scale 
  Set and periodically check your powder charge, we recommend one of the following: 
  • Dillon D-Terminator electronic scale (DLN-10483), and protective case (CED-SCase)
  • Dillon Eliminator balance-beam scale (DLN-13480)
  • CED Universal digital pocket scale (CED-UDPS)
  • Loading Manual
  • RDM’s Somchem reloading manual, version 2 (SomchemManual) is the only manual to include data for local, South African propellants.
  • DVD: Competition Reloading with Brian Enos (DLN-14341) - a step-by-step guide through the reloading process for IPSC, Steel Challenge and other action-shooting styles.
  • Safety Glasses 

You should always protect your eyes when reloading. Primers contain explosive compounds and nitrocellulose propellant is extremely flammable, with explosive characteristics when burning in a confined volume. We recommend:

  • Draeger X-pect safety glasses (Xpect) are made of tough, clear polycarbonate for indoor use, like reloading.
  • Rudy Project Rydon glasses (Rydon) are made of super-tough ImpactX material for superior protection, while reloading or when shooting. 
  • Vernier calliper 

Set and check cartridge dimensions, like crimp and overall length, we recommend:

  • CED digital calliper (CED-DigiCal). The calliper is not absolutely essential, but close enough that we included it here!
technical_specifications:
Ram diameter 1½” 
Loading rate
  • 1 000 to 1 200 rounds per hour
Height (from bench)
  • 38" (~960mm) with the electric case feeder installed.
Capacity
  • Extra Small Powder Bar -  throws from ½ grain to about 3 grains
  • Small Powder Bar - throws from a little under 3 grains to about 20 grains of powder.
  • Large Powder Bar - throws from around 15 grains to nearly 45 grains of extruded type propellant, and from around 20 to about 50 grains of ball/spherical type propellant.
  • Magnum Powder Bar - throws up to ~73 grains of extruded type propellant and ~82 grains of ball/spherical type propellant (not generally required for the Super 1050). 

NOTE: Capacities depend on actual propellant type, the values listed here are approximate.

name: Boeshield T-9 Lubricant - 30ml bottle
description:
The Boeshield T-9 Lubricant is a highly advanced waterproof lubrication that dries to a thin waxy film. Spray or apply to your metal surfaces to prevent rust, corrosion, and dirt accumulation. As it is a dry lubricant, it is suitable for your sport firearms or EDC gun. The Boeshield T-9 Lubricant is a highly advanced waterproof lubrication that dries to a thin waxy film. Spray or apply to your metal surfaces to prevent rust, corrosion, and dirt accumulation. Since it is a dry lubricant, it is suitable for your sport firearms or EDC gun.

Boeshield T-9 is a dry lubricant that can be used on the outside of hand guns, as it will not leave an oily residue on your clothes. It also provides long lasting lubrication on all moving parts, due to its unique formulation of solvent carrier and paraffin wax coating. T-9 was engineered to penetrate crevices deeply, displace moisture, dissolve minor corrosion, and leave a waxy coating with lasting durability. T-9 does not contain: Teflon, silicone, fluorocarbons, MEK, or acetone. You can use T-9 to protect the top of your gun from rusting, especially if you carry it in a holster for most of the day.

Boeshield T-9 may be used on the slide mechanism of handguns, the outside of a firearm, the inside and outside of the barrel, the cylinders of revolvers, and cartridge cases as a case lube.

key_features:
Cleans - Attacks existing corrosion, loosens rusty parts and flushes out old lubricants

 

Easy and fast lubrication - Spray on and wipe off the excess for immediate use, dries to a waxy, waterproof finish without leaving a sticky film to attract dirt, dust or mud

 

Reaches deeper - Stays liquid long enough to permeate metal crevices and leave a durable protective coating that lubricates and protects

 

Long-term protection - Apply to any metal surface and let it dry, providing lubrication that endures, month after month

 

Completely waterproof - dries to a clean, waxy, waterproof film that won’t wash off in rain or mud. You can rinse away sand, dust and grime with water, while leaving the lubricant intact.

 

Tough but safe - T-9 will not harm wood, paint, plastic, rubber, fiberglass or vinyl.

 

Perfect for coastal areas - is particularly effective for use in protecting all metals in salt water coastal areas.

Easy and fast lubrication - Spray on and wipe off the excess for immediate use, dries to a waxy, waterproof finish without leaving a sticky film to attract dirt, dust or mud

 

Reaches deeper - Stays liquid long enough to permeate metal crevices and leave a durable protective coating that lubricates and protects

 

Long-term protection - Apply to any metal surface and let it dry, providing lubrication that endures, month after month

 

Completely waterproof - dries to a clean, waxy, waterproof film that won’t wash off in rain or mud. You can rinse away sand, dust and grime with water, while leaving the lubricant intact.

 

Tough but safe - T-9 will not harm wood, paint, plastic, rubber, fiberglass or vinyl.

 

Perfect for coastal areas - is particularly effective for use in protecting all metals in salt water coastal areas.

name: Boeshield T-9 Lubricant -120ml aerosol
description:
The Boeshield T-9 Lubricant is a highly advanced waterproof lubrication that dries to a thin waxy film. Spray or apply to your metal surfaces to prevent rust, corrosion, and dirt accumulation. As it is a dry lubricant, it is suitable for your sport firearms or EDC gun. The Boeshield T-9 Lubricant is a highly advanced waterproof lubrication that dries to a thin waxy film. Spray or apply to your metal surfaces to prevent rust, corrosion, and dirt accumulation. Since it is a dry lubricant, it is suitable for your sport firearms or EDC gun.

Boeshield T-9 is a dry lubricant that can be used on the outside of hand guns, as it will not leave an oily residue on your clothes. It also provides long lasting lubrication on all moving parts, due to its unique formulation of solvent carrier and paraffin wax coating. T-9 was engineered to penetrate crevices deeply, displace moisture, dissolve minor corrosion, and leave a waxy coating with lasting durability. T-9 does not contain: Teflon, silicone, fluorocarbons, MEK, or acetone. You can use T-9 to protect the top of your gun from rusting, especially if you carry it in a holster for most of the day.

Boeshield T-9 may be used on the slide mechanism of handguns, the outside of a firearm, the inside and outside of the barrel, the cylinders of revolvers, and cartridge cases as a case lube.

name: Dillon SL 900 Recommended Setup for 12 Gauge
description:
The Dillon SL 900 Recommended Setup for 12 gauge is a progressive reloader capable of loading 600 to 800 rounds of 12ga shotgun ammo per hour. Shooting Stuff has included the most popular options and safety features for the SL 900.

The Dillon SL 900 has been designed to reliably load shot with a diameter smaller than #5; 3.1mm. It is important to ensure that your shot is properly spherical, uniform in size and adequately lubricated with graphite powder.

For complete peace of mind, the SL 900 is covered by Dillon’s legendary Lifetime "No-B.S." warranty. All electrical & electronic components in Dillon equipment are covered by a one-year warranty, as are textiles. Shooting Stuff fully supports Dillon’s warranty and has a spares cupboard with most spare parts available in stock. 

Click here to review a full description of the SL 900 and the many available options.
short_description: The Dillon SL 900 Recommended Setup for 12 gauge is a progressive reloader capable of loading 600 to 800 rounds of 12ga shotgun ammo per hour. Shooting Stuff has included the most popular options and safety features for the SL 900.
meta_title: Dillon SL 900 Comprehensive Setup for 12 Gauge | Reloading Presses | Shooting Stuff
meta_description: Looking for Dillon SL 900 Comprehensive Setup for 12 Gauge? Shooting Stuff has a large range of shooting products and accessories. Buy online today!
calibre_conversion:
Shooting Stuff has pre-configured this package for you for just one calibre, 12 Gauge. Your Dillon SL 900 can load 20 and 28 Gauge calibres. Calibre Conversion on the SL 900 is both as quick and easy as you want to make it. Dillon offers various levels of convenience to suit your requirements and budget. 

Option 1 - Minimum Kit 

As a minimum, you will need the following to change calibres:

  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
Option 2 - Convenient Conversion

Option 1 does not take full advantage of the convenience offered by the SL 900's interchangeable tool head. So, if you want to leave your dies pre-set, you'll need:

  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.

Depending on what calibre you are going to, and where you are changing from, you may also need a different case feed plate for the electric case feeder. Please refer to the calibre conversion chart in the Instruction Manual for the correct plate. The SL 900 Instruction Manual can be downloaded here, or call Shooting Stuff for advice. Available case feed plates (applicable to the SL 900) are:

  • 12 Gauge Casefeed plate (DLN-17811)
  • 20/28 Gauge Casefeed plate (DLN-97045)
We call this “calibre conversion, the moderately easy way” and believe that a case gauge for the specific calibre would be a good idea!
Option 3 - The Easy Way 

For the full Dillon convenience of changing calibres “the easy way” consider the option to leave your dies, powder system and powder check system set up and dedicated to a specific cartridge for faster, easier calibre changes. We call this “calibre conversion, the easy way”

  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
  • Tool head stand (DLN-22055)
  • Quick-change Dust Cover (DLN-11143) keeps the assembled tool head with powder measure dust free.

Depending on what calibre you are going to, and where you are changing from, you may also need a different case feed plate for the electric case feeder. Please refer to the calibre conversion chart in the Instruction Manual for the correct plate. The SL 900 Instruction Manual can be downloaded here, or call Shooting Stuff for advice. Available case feed plates (applicable to the SL 900) are:

  • 12 Gauge Casefeed plate (DLN-17811)
  • 20/28 Gauge Casefeed plate (DLN-97045)
key_features:
• The SL 900 is a 5-station, progressive reloading machine:
    • Station 1: Insert hull into shell plate (at the bottom), resize and de-prime (at the top)
    • Station 2: Seat a new primer (at the bottom) and dispense propellant (at the top)
    • Station 3: Insert plastic wad into hull (at the bottom) and dispense shot (at the top)
    • Station 4: Hull is formed and folded (at the top)
    • Station 5: Final crimp and seating closing the top (at the top)
  • Insert hull automatically.
  • Index the shell plate automatically.
  • Feed and insert new primers automatically.
  • Dispense propellant automatically.
  • Operator places wads manually.
  • Eject loaded shot shells automatically.
  • Setup for 12 gauge, but can load 20 and 28 gauge calibres (requires additional calibre-specific items).
  • Interchangeable tool head, for easy calibre conversion.
optional_accesories: Click here for a comprehensive list of optional accessories
package_contents:
Shooting Stuff's Recommended SL 900 system comprises the following:

  • SL 900 Machine
 This is "the big white box" that includes the main reloading machine and 
  • SL 900 tool head and frame with calibre-specific parts for 12 Gauge
  • Operating handle
  • Powder measure
  • Shot dispenser
  • Shotshell chute
  • SL 900 hardware bag
  • SL 900 accessory bag
  • Case feed mounting post and Case Feed Tube
  • Shot hopper post and hopper
  • Printed Instruction Manual
  • SL 900 Strong Mount
  • Loaded cartridge bin (blue, plastic AkroBin)
  • SL 900 Case Feeder
 220V electric case feeder with a case feeder plate. True convenience!
  • Toolkit
 Shooting Stuff's Toolkit for the SL900 is a stylish, one-piece bracket that mounts to the "blue" Dillon progressive reloading machines to organise and store a set of ball-ended Allen wrenches and the 1-inch spanner.
  • Spare Parts Kit
 A collection of small parts that could easily get lost, or break, consider the Spare Parts Kit your insurance package until the Dillon Lifetime No-B.S. Warranty kicks in. After all, Murphy's Law states that if something can go wrong it will, and at the worst possible time (like the night before your match)
  • Setup

We will gladly setup your machine for you for FREE, as far as possible.

  • If you collect from us we can fully assemble the machine and included accessories, and then adjust the dies and powder charge.
  • If we ship the kit to you via courier, the extent of the setup is limited since we need to re-package the kit for safe shipping. We can install and adjust the dies, and set the powder charge, but you'll need to assemble all the bits.

Please add notes when checking out & finalising your purchase that include your load details, or send us an e-mail once your order is confirmed. If you want to assemble and setup everything yourself, learning the most about your machine, just omit the notes at check-out - simple!
required_accesories:
You will also need the following items (not included with this kit) to reload:

  • Scale 

Set and periodically check your powder charge, we recommend one of the following: 

  • Dillon D-Terminator electronic scale (DLN-10483), and protective case (CED-SCase)
  • Dillon Eliminator balance-beam scale (DLN-13480)
  • CED Universal digital pocket scale (CED-UDPS)
  • Loading Manual
  • RDM’s Somchem reloading manual, version 2 (SomchemManual) is the only manual to include data for local, South African propellants.
  • Safety Glasses 

You should always protect your eyes when reloading. Primers contain explosive compounds and nitrocellulose propellant is extremely flammable, with explosive characteristics when burning in a confined volume. We recommend:

  • Draeger X-pect safety glasses (Xpect) are made of tough, clear polycarbonate for indoor use, like reloading.
  • Rudy Project Rydon glasses (Rydon) are made of super-tough ImpactX material for superior protection, while reloading or when shooting. 
  • Vernier calliper 

Set and check cartridge dimensions, like crimp and overall length, we recommend:

  • CED digital calliper (CED-DigiCal). The calliper is not absolutely essential, but close enough that we included it here!
technical_specifications:
Ram diameter 1½” 
Loading rate
  • 600 to 800 rounds per hour
Height (from bench)
  • Without the optional electric case feeder: 49" (~1250mm) 
  • With the electric case feeder installed: 38½" (~980mm) 
Capacity
  • Large Powder Bar - throws from 15 to nearly 45 grains of extruded type propellant, and from 20 to about 50 grains of ball/spherical type propellant.
  • Standard shot bar - thows 1 1/4 oz of lead shot
  • Small gauge shot bar - thows 1/2-1 oz of  lead shot
NOTE: Capacities depend on actual propellant type, the values listed here are approximate.

package_contents:
Shooting Stuff's recommended XL 650 system comprises the following:

  • XL 650 Machine
 This is "the big white box" that includes the main reloading machine and 
  • Calibre Conversion Kit Box, with calibre-specific parts for 9mm Luger
  • Primer early warning system
  • Operating handle, with knob
  • Powder measure
  • 650 Primer System Parts Bag
  • 650 Accessory Box
  • Case feed mounting post and Case Feed Tube
  • Printed Instruction Manual
  • XL 650 Case Feeder
 220V electric case feeder with a small-pistol case feeder plate. True convenience!
  • Dillon 9mm Carbide Die Set

3-die set for progressive relaoding machines:

  • Carbide sizing die with decapping assembly
  • Bullet seating die
  • Separate taper crimp die
  • Powder Check System
 Once properly adjusted, this sensor verifies a safe charge in each and every case during the loading process.
  • Machine Mount
 Shooting Stuff's blue, powder coated machine mount raises the entire XL 650 above the bench's top, and spreads the load. A more stable system simply loads better! If necessary, the assembled 650-system stands securely on the machine mount.
  • Bullet Tray
 Dillon's cast Bullet Tray mounts to the left plate of the machine mount, and holds a few hundred bullets conveniently close to where they're needed.
  • Toolkit
 Shooting Stuff's Toolkit for the XL650 is a stylish, one-piece bracket that mounts to the "blue" Dillon progressive reloading machines to organise and store a set of ball-ended Allen wrenches and the 1-inch spanner. These tools are supplied in the kit and are what's required to adjust and basically service the machine.
  • Primer Flip Tray
  Dillon's metal flip tray is used to quickly get primers "the right way up" after dispensing these from their tray. 
  • Primer Pick-up Tubes
 A pack of 4 additional primer pick-up tubes used to pick-up small primers from the Flip Tray. Together with the one included with the reloading machine you'll be able to pre-fill 500 primers so that you can conveniently load a substantail batch of ammo with minimum interuption to replenish components.
  • Case lube
 While not absolutely essential when using carbide dies, we highly recommend Dillon's easy-to-apply, spray-on case lube. Trust us on this - you'll feel the difference!
  • DVD Instruction Manual
 Video conveys so much more than printed pictures and text. You won't find this info on YouTube!
  • Case Gauge

name: Dillon SL 900 Sensible Minimum Setup for 12 Gauge
description:
The Dillon SL 900 Sensible Minimum Setup for 12 gauge is a progressive reloader capable of loading 600 to 800 rounds of 12ga shotgun ammo per hour. Shooting Stuff has included the most essential options for you to start loading on the SL 900.

The Dillon SL 900 has been designed to reliably load shot with a diameter smaller than #5; 3.1mm. It is important to ensure that your shot is properly spherical, uniform in size and adequately lubricated with graphite powder.

For complete peace of mind, the SL 900 is covered by Dillon’s legendary Lifetime "No-B.S." warranty. All electrical & electronic components in Dillon equipment are covered by a one-year warranty, as are textiles. Shooting Stuff fully supports Dillon’s warranty and has a spares cupboard with most spare parts available in stock. 

Click here to review a full description of the SL 900 and the many available options.
short_description: The Dillon SL 900 Sensible Minimum Setup for 12 gauge is a progressive reloader capable of loading 600 to 800 rounds of 12ga shotgun ammo per hour. Shooting Stuff has included the most essential options for you to start loading on the SL 900.

calibre_conversion:
Shooting Stuff has pre-configured this package for you for just one calibre, 12 Gauge. Your Dillon SL 900 can load 20 and 28 Gauge calibres. Calibre Conversion on the SL 900 is both as quick and easy as you want to make it. Dillon offers various levels of convenience to suit your requirements and budget. 

Option 1 - Minimum Kit 

As a minimum, you will need the following to change calibres:

  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
Option 2 - Convenient Conversion

Option 1 does not take full advantage of the convenience offered by the SL 900's interchangeable tool head. So, if you want to leave your dies pre-set, you'll need:

  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.

Depending on what calibre you are going to, and where you are changing from, you may also need a different case feed plate for the electric case feeder. Please refer to the calibre conversion chart in the Instruction Manual for the correct plate. The SL 900 Instruction Manual can be downloaded here, or call Shooting Stuff for advice. Available case feed plates (applicable to the SL 900) are:

  • 12 Gauge Casefeed plate (DLN-17811)
  • 20/28 Gauge Casefeed plate (DLN-97045)
We call this “calibre conversion, the moderately easy way” and believe that a case gauge for the specific calibre would be a good idea!
Option 3 - The Easy Way 

For the full Dillon convenience of changing calibres “the easy way” consider the option to leave your dies, powder system and powder check system set up and dedicated to a specific cartridge for faster, easier calibre changes. We call this “calibre conversion, the easy way”

  • Calibre Conversion Kit for the specific calibre.
  • Tool head stand (DLN-22055)
  • Quick-change Dust Cover (DLN-11143) keeps the assembled tool head with powder measure dust free.

Depending on what calibre you are going to, and where you are changing from, you may also need a different case feed plate for the electric case feeder. Please refer to the calibre conversion chart in the Instruction Manual for the correct plate. The SL 900 Instruction Manual can be downloaded here, or call Shooting Stuff for advice. Available case feed plates (applicable to the SL 900) are:

  • 12 Gauge Casefeed plate (DLN-17811)
  • 20/28 Gauge Casefeed plate (DLN-97045)
key_features:
• The SL 900 is a 5-station, progressive reloading machine:
    • Station 1: Insert hull into shell plate (at the bottom), resize and de-prime (at the top)
    • Station 2: Seat a new primer (at the bottom) and dispense propellant (at the top)
    • Station 3: Insert plastic wad into hull (at the bottom) and dispense shot (at the top)
    • Station 4: Hull is formed and folded (at the top)
    • Station 5: Final crimp and seating closing the top (at the top)
  • Insert hull automatically.
  • Index the shell plate automatically.
  • Feed and insert new primers automatically.
  • Dispense propellant automatically.
  • Operator places wads manually.
  • Eject loaded shot shells automatically.
  • Setup for 12 gauge, but can load 20 and 28 gauge calibres (requires additional calibre-specific items).
  • Interchangeable tool head, for easy calibre conversion.

package_contents:
Shooting Stuff's sensible minimum SL 900 system comprises the following:

  • SL 900 Machine
 This is "the big white box" that includes the main reloading machine and 
  • SL 900 tool head and frame with calibre-specific parts for 12 Gauge
  • Operating handle
  • Powder measure
  • Shot dispenser
  • Shotshell chute
  • SL 900 hardware bag
  • SL 900 accessory bag
  • Case feed mounting post and Case Feed Tube
  • Shot hopper post and hopper
  • Printed Instruction Manual
  • SL 900 Strong Mount
  • Loaded cartridge bin (blue, plastic AkroBin)
  • 1" Spanner
 Shooting Stuff's 1-inch spanner gets in to the small space available on the tool head so that you can adjust the dies as required. Conventional spanners and shifters are just too bulky!
  • Spare Parts Kit
 A collection of small parts that could easily get lost, or break, consider the Spare Parts Kit your insurance package until the Dillon Lifetime No-B.S. Warranty kicks in. After all, Murphy's Law states that if something can go wrong it will, and at the worst possible time (like the night before your match)
  • Setup

We will gladly setup your machine for you for FREE, as far as possible.

  • If you collect from us we can fully assemble the machine and included accessories, and then adjust the dies and powder charge.
  • If we ship the kit to you via courier, the extent of the setup is limited since we need to re-package the kit for safe shipping. We can install and adjust the dies, and set the powder charge, but you'll need to assemble all the bits.

Please add notes when checking out & finalising your purchase that include your load details, or send us an e-mail once your order is confirmed. If you want to assemble and setup everything yourself, learning the most about your machine, just omit the notes at check-out - simple!
required_accesories:
You will also need the following items (not included with this kit) to reload:

  • Scale 

Set and periodically check your powder charge, we recommend one of the following: 

  • Dillon D-Terminator electronic scale (DLN-10483), and protective case (CED-SCase)
  • Dillon Eliminator balance-beam scale (DLN-13480)
  • CED Universal digital pocket scale (CED-UDPS)
  • Loading Manual
  • RDM’s Somchem reloading manual, version 2 (SomchemManual) is the only manual to include data for local, South African propellants.
  • Safety Glasses 

You should always protect your eyes when reloading. Primers contain explosive compounds and nitrocellulose propellant is extremely flammable, with explosive characteristics when burning in a confined volume. We recommend:

  • Draeger X-pect safety glasses (Xpect) are made of tough, clear polycarbonate for indoor use, like reloading.
  • Rudy Project Rydon glasses (Rydon) are made of super-tough ImpactX material for superior protection, while reloading or when shooting. 
  • Vernier calliper 

Set and check cartridge dimensions, like crimp and overall length, we recommend:

  • CED digital calliper (CED-DigiCal). The calliper is not absolutely essential, but close enough that we included it here!
technical_specifications:
Ram diameter 1½” 
Loading rate
  • 600 to 800 rounds per hour
Height (from bench)
  • Without the optional electric case feeder: 49" (~1250mm) 
  • With the electric case feeder installed: 38½" (~980mm) 
Capacity
  • Large Powder Bar - throws from 15 to nearly 45 grains of extruded type propellant, and from 20 to about 50 grains of ball/spherical type propellant.
  • Standard shot bar - thows 1 1/4 oz of lead shot
  • Small gauge shot bar - thows 1/2-1 oz of  lead shot
NOTE: Capacities depend on actual propellant type, the values listed here are approximate.

name: Dillon RL 550B Progressive Reloading Kit
description:
The Dillon RL 550B is a 4-station, manually indexed progressive reloading machine capable of reloading most popular handgun and rifle calibres, up to the likes of .375 H&H;, .338 Lapua Magnum, etc.  This machine can load up to 400 to 600 rounds per hour, and over 800 rounds per hour when using the optional electric case feeder. 

The machine stations work as follow:

1. Resize & Deprime / Prime
  • The cartridge case is manually inserted into the shell plate (at the bottom).
  • When using the optional electric case feeder, the cases are automatically fed from the case feeder tube into the shell plate.
  • When the handle is lowered, raising the platform and shell plate to the dies in the tool head, the case enters the first die and is resized and de-primed (at the top).
  • The handle is raised, lowering the platform and the cartridge case is then primed (at the bottom)
  • The shell plate is manually indexed, to end the cycle.
2. Powder Drop / Flare
  • On the next cycle, as the handle is lowered, raising the platform and shell plate to the dies in the tool head, the case enters the powder die and is flared or “belled” (at the top) and powder dispensed (only if a case is present)
  • NOTE: The flaring action is not applicable to most rifle calibres.
3. Seat
  • The bullet is manually positioned in the case mouth (at the bottom)
  • As the handle is lowered, raising the platform and shell plate to the dies in the tool head, the case and bullet enter the seating die where the bullet is seated to the desired depth to achieve a suitable overall length of the cartridge.
4. Crimp
  • When the case enters the final die (at the top) a taper crimp is applied to remove the flare that was applied at station 2 and to suitably grip the bullet.
  • The crimp is especially important for semi-automatic firearms to ensure safe and reliable feeding from the magazine into the chamber.
  • The case is automatically ejected into the cartridge bin after the handle has been raised and the machine is manually indexed.

The RL 550B is covered by Dillon’s legendary Lifetime 'No-B.S' warranty. Shooting Stuff fully supports this warranty and has a spares cupboard with most spare parts available in stock. Please note that electric / electronic items and textiles have a 1-year warranty.
